	quest.02E43399D22E3673.quest_subtitle: "Witness oblivion and forge yourself anew"
	quest.02ED95A33E2605E7.quest_desc: [
		"A sinister familiar devoted to the study of toxins and decay."
		"It specializes in poison magic, weakening enemies and letting them suffer a slow death."
		""
		"&9Abilities:&r"
		""
		"• You and the Plague Doctor deal increased damage to poisoned enemies."
		""
		"• When the Plague Doctor is hit, it throws a poison potion as a countermeasure."
		""
		"&dCreation:&r"
		""
		"Craft a &2Poison Vial&r and give it to a tamed Druid Familiar to transform it into a Plague Doctor."
	]
	quest.02ED95A33E2605E7.quest_subtitle: "Master of Venoms"
	quest.02ED95A33E2605E7.title: "Plague Doctor"
	quest.02F5B1D547CCF693.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/grudels_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.02FA2B11318F6A46.quest_desc: [
		"There is a forum on our discord where you can suggest mods for &6Integrated Minecraft&r. Feel free to post your thought there. Be prepared for the suggestion to be denied, however. As a general rule of thumb, it's better to have less mods than more, as if we discover any game-breaking bugs, removing mods can break player's worlds."
		""
		"That said, we highly highly encourage you to customize the pack to your wants and needs. To do this, in CurseForge, go to the dots next to &6\"Play\"&r, hit &6\"Profile Options\"&r, and click &6\"Allow Content Management for this Profile\"&r. Most mods should be compatible out of the box. "
		""
		"&cALWAYS BACKUP YOUR PACK BEFORE ADDING, REMOVING, OR UPDATING MODS.&r"
	]
	quest.030516DFAE42395F.quest_desc: [
		"Allows you to store enchantments that can then be transferred into an item."
		""
		"Only works with &bsuper enchantments&r that go beyond vanilla level 30+."
	]
