	quest.2978C7CA72D4A23F.quest_desc: [
		"A cunning familiar that manipulates perception and confuses enemies."
		""
		"&9Abilities:&r"
		""
		"• When the owner is low on health, it can conceal them from enemies."
		""
		"• When critically injured, it vanishes and leaves behind an explosive decoy."
		""
		"&dHabitat:&r"
		""
		"Illusionists often gather within &7Woodland Mansions&r."
	]
	quest.2978C7CA72D4A23F.quest_subtitle: "Master of Deception"
	quest.2978C7CA72D4A23F.title: "Illusionist"
	quest.29798FB8B31D0A24.quest_desc: [
		"Once upon a time, a war broke out between several villager castles and kingdoms. After the war was over, one such kingdom created a grand crypt to honor their fallen soldiers, chief among them the &3Paladin General. &rHowever, a &5witch&r scorned and exiled from the village became enraged upon hearing this. These were the very same soldiers that ran her out into the wilderness. "
		""
		"In an act of revenge, the &5witch&r destroyed the kingdom and cursed the crypt so that the soldiers may never find rest. Now their spirits haunt the hallways of the crypt, protecting the innermost sanctum in which the late &3Paladin&r remains. Legend says that should the &3Possessed Paladin&r be vanquished, the curse will lift and the soldiers will find peace at last."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Possessed Paladin is found in the Abandoned Crypt in the &2Overworld&r. Use an &6Eye of Ghost&r to locate it."
	]
	quest.2987F83C7A21D8DD.title: "Blackwood Taiga"
	quest.29A02D88684E3B14.title: "Tyr Armor"
	quest.29A9F5E23FCB78F5.quest_desc: [
		"Simple enchanting may not be enough."
		"Reforge your equipment to gain additional effects."
		""
		"Item rarity ranges from &9Rare&r to &dEpic&r and up to &6Mythic&r, each tier providing stronger bonuses."
		""
		"Unlocks &6Item Reforging&r chapter."
	]
	quest.29A9F5E23FCB78F5.quest_subtitle: "Equipment upgrades"
	quest.29A9F5E23FCB78F5.title: "Reforging Basics"
	quest.29D68A5F93C753A1.quest_desc: [
		"A hybrid between a warped fungus and an enderman, the &3Warped Fungusses&r is a product of its environment. This creature was first spotted by a piglin explorer. When an enderman teleported partially into a giant warped fungus, they fused together and became the &3Warped Fungusses.&r Now, although still rare, there are more &3Warped Fungussi&r wandering the warped forests. Occasionally, they are even known to make a den. Though it’s best to leave immediately should one stumble into a den as &3Warped Fungussi&r are very protective and territorial."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Warped Fungusses spawns rarely throughout &3warped biomes&r in the &4Nether. &r"
	]
	quest.2A0A01BE836BB2AB.quest_desc: ["A monument of grandeur and mystery, the Shiraz Palace sprawls in every direction, its halls twisting and turning beyond comprehension. Its purpose remains unknown, but its size and opulence are undeniable. Travelers beware: without a companion, it’s all too easy to lose your way in this labyrinthine estate."]
	quest.2A0A01BE836BB2AB.quest_subtitle: "Find the Shiraz Palace"
	quest.2A1B0386B7987DD3.quest_desc: ["Vast and dreamlike, the Aviary stretches high into wtilight sky, its halls divided into four whimsical quadrants. Each one unfolds as a surreal scene—bright, strange, and perilous in its own way. To wander here feels like stepping beyond reality itself. Is this the journey’s end… or just another beginning?"]
	quest.2A1B0386B7987DD3.quest_subtitle: "Find an Aviary"
	quest.2A26CDEDDE63B59A.quest_desc: ["&5Thread&r can use to craft many buffs to be applied to magical armor with an &5Alteration table&r. First, place armor on table and place &5Thread&r in it, (make sure you had the required tier for the &5Thread&r you using) remove armor when finished."]
	quest.2A26CDEDDE63B59A.quest_subtitle: "Not a normal thread, this one contains magic!"
	quest.2A26CDEDDE63B59A.title: "Magic Thread"
	quest.2A48B9F31BC1B3F6.title: "Glistering Meadow"
	quest.2A4C4E78F52E7349.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Storage Controller&r allows multiple storages to function as a single network."
		""
		"Containers placed next to each other automatically form this network."
		"Right-click the &6Storage Controller&r with an item to insert it, and it will be sorted into the correct container."
		""
		"The &6Storage Controller&r can also connect wirelessly to &6Storage Links&r within a range of &615 blocks&r."
	]
	quest.2A4C4E78F52E7349.quest_subtitle: "Centralized storage"
	quest.2A621F9949186B1D.quest_subtitle: "Have every potion effect applied at the same time."
	quest.2A704F47861FA750.title: "Dark Forest"
	quest.2A9727EBE40E6ED3.quest_desc: ["Rare plants need a special vessel to grow. Enchanted Ash and soul residue mixed into the soil make the right environment, though it cannot sustain common crops."]
	quest.2A9E88C201991AE2.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/sppinto_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.2ABC9EFB107F38CC.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/spider_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.2AD640E46A4B5685.quest_desc: [
		"The &5Mother of the Maze&r is an ancient sea monster that does not like to be disturbed. You will know she is nearby when you feel the vibrations in the water beneath your feet. You may want a special set of diving gear to protect you from the icy cold waters as you fight her."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The &5Mother of the Maze&r will periodically spawn as you explore the &bIce Maze&r. Enter the water after you see the message &6“You feel a vibration under the ice…”&r to find and fight her."
	]
	quest.2AD908646819FE10.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5Once a Decaying relic awakened at the deep!"
	quest.2AE34D8173EA2A79.quest_desc: [
		"Certain materials transform when exposed to soul energy."
		"These byproducts are used in advanced rituals and crafting."
		""
		"&8●&r &bAstral Weave&r — Phantom Membrane infused with soul energy."
		"A mystic cloth that can bind the flow of arcana."
		""
		"&8●&r &bGrim Talc&r — Bones crystallized by soul exposure."
		"Can be processed or used as a ritual component."
		""
		"&8●&r &bRotting Essence&r — Undead flesh warped by soul energy."
		"Toxic, unstable, used in darker infusions."
		""
		"&8●&r &bWarp Flux&r — Residual magic condensed from endermen."
		"Disruptive essence used in high-tier arcane crafting."
		""
		"These materials are required for advanced pacts and rituals."
	]
	quest.2AE34D8173EA2A79.quest_subtitle: "Soul-altered materials"
	quest.2AE34D8173EA2A79.title: "Esoteric Reaping"
	quest.2AE36C2E5368AC7D.quest_desc: [
		"&8● &6Power Transfer&r"
		"Allows rotational power to split into multiple directions."
		""
		"The standard Gearbox transfers power horizontally."
		"The Vertical Gearbox performs the same function but vertically."
		""
		"&8● &6Rotation&r"
		"Power enters through the side with the shaft."
		""
		"The other three sides output rotation."
		"The output direction is always reversed."
	]
	quest.2AE36C2E5368AC7D.quest_subtitle: "Power transmission"
	quest.2AF547C932FF6A42.quest_desc: ["Defeat the Dead King to become able to revive Familiars upon death"]
	quest.2AF547C932FF6A42.quest_subtitle: "Bringing Familiars back to life"
	quest.2B290D14C4F667DF.quest_desc: ["Basic, cheap, effiency start is what make a better end."]
	quest.2B290D14C4F667DF.title: "First things first"
	quest.2B35D32FDE714347.quest_desc: ["Who say mage can't go combat? wear this!"]
	quest.2B35D32FDE714347.title: "Ignis Mage"
	quest.2B39CEA553B62683.title: "Pumpkin Fields"
	quest.2B4A9CFD716B5475.quest_desc: ["More complex &eCreate&r components are crafted with precision machines. These machines are made by deploying a cogwheel, large cogwheel, and iron ingot (in that order) 5 times. Because these are so difficult to make, however, there is a chance that it will not succeed and you will instead get another item."]
	quest.2B4A9CFD716B5475.title: "Precision Machine"
	quest.2B5C13373769BEC0.quest_desc: [
		"A warrior Angel once upon a time who became corrupted by power and greed. Kicked out of its celestial home and forced to live in a &bFrosted Prison&r in the Overworld, &bMaledictus&r became a tyrannical lord. Eventually all the citizens nearby fled leaving only &bMaledictus&r and his most faithful warriors behind. Now &bMaledictus&r spends his days asleep, dreaming of his return home where he plans to wage war on those who wronged him."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"To wake Maledictus, r-click on his grave within the Frosted Prison in the &2Overworld&r. Use an &6Eye of Curse&r to locate the Frosted Prison."
	]
	quest.2B6C3E55D794D9BC.title: "Sentiel Archer"
	quest.2B70445E6CD99EDB.quest_desc: [
		"Strange structures have begun rising from the land. Mysterious dungeons, fortresses, and towers that pierce the skies. No one knows where they came from, only that they’re teeming with hostile creatures, forgotten treasures, and powerful secrets."
		""
		"Your task is to venture forth and uncover the mysteries of these ancient places. Each dungeon holds new dangers, but also the keys to survival: weapons, artifacts, and knowledge that will aid you in the trials ahead."
		""
		"Prepare yourself adventurer. &6Exploration&r and courage are the only ways to thrive in this world where the land itself rises against you."
	]
	quest.2B8CF1D521BD6EF2.quest_desc: [
		"Trade &bEmeralds&r for &bMaps&r to locate some structures!"
		""
		"&eNot all structures have maps that can be purchased.&r Complete quests in the exploration chapter to earn maps to structures that don't appear here."
		""
		"You can also use &6Locator Eyes&r to find some dungeons instead of using maps. These are typically for bosses."
	]
	quest.2B8CF1D521BD6EF2.quest_subtitle: "Your One-Stop Cartography Shop"
	quest.2B8CF1D521BD6EF2.title: "Finding Structures"
	quest.2B8FC7867EEAAD0A.title: "Owl Post Office"
	quest.2BB6A49989FA23DF.title: "Warm Ocean"
	quest.2BD3F2C24A49E814.title: "Farmhouse"
	quest.2BD5481BAC57878D.quest_desc: [
		"The &bImpurity Stabilizer&r uses &#792CECWicked&r energy in a controlled way."
		""
		"It grants a strong percentage bonus to the weakest Crucible attribute."
		""
		"Fuel usage and instability are not affected."
		""
		"Tuning strain increases slightly."
	]
	quest.2BD5481BAC57878D.quest_subtitle: "Empower the weakest"
	quest.2BEC97498707196B.quest_desc: [
		"Illagers are the common enemy against villagers. And with their newfound leader, it has only gotten worse. The &3Adjudicator&r can be found meditating in his study in the basement below the newly renovated &2Woodland Mansion&r. He will wake from his meditation upon the player attacking him or breaking any blocks. He uses a variety of magic such as teleportation and magic weapons. Should you find him too difficult, leave him be and he will return to meditating. But the dark forest will never be free until he is slain. "
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The &2Woodland Mansion&r is located in &2Dark Forest&r biomes. The &3Adjudicator&r will only ever stay in the basement of this structure."
	]
	quest.2C05F96AABB60896.title: "Witches' Abode"
	quest.2C68C07B2D834C8C.quest_desc: [
		"Created in a vicious clash between sea and sky, &3Scylla&r is a product of both. She harnesses the powers of water and lightning to destroy those that that enter her home, a floating &bAcropolis&r anchored to the ocean below. Many historians believe that the legends of &3Scylla&r are what inspored the journeys of other infamous sailors like &3Captain Cornelia."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Scylla's anchor weapon Ceraunus is found at the top of the Acropolis in the &2Overworld&r. R-click the anchor to awaken her. Use an &6Eye of Storm&r to locate the Acropolis."
	]
	quest.2C8ED6929770CAD9.quest_desc: ["A combat support unit build for people who are not high skill or want to go with low cost"]
	quest.2CB7084AB351F379.title: "Hermit's Hollow"
	quest.2CCAC39F67E06944.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Fishing Net&r can be mounted on a rotating contraption placed in water."
		"While spinning, it passively collects fish."
	]
	quest.2CCAC39F67E06944.quest_subtitle: "Automatic fishing"
	quest.2CCBAF7F8AAB2F69.title: "Upside Down Forest"
	quest.2D0BF4AA6BE0F6E6.quest_desc: [
		"&#1E5AA8Advanced Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it strikes weakened monsters."
		"The rite delivers a devastating blow to both soul and body."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
		"[&#CB0CF8✧&r] &#CB0CF8Eldritch&r"
	]
	quest.2D0BF4AA6BE0F6E6.quest_subtitle: "Strike the vulnerable"
	quest.2D58F257908A4162.title: "Temperate Grove"
	quest.2D626A2E1004F5C1.quest_desc: [
		"The &2Ancient Guardian&r is a creature of the earth (lowercase “e”, because obviously we are from &2the Overworld&r and not some random planet called Earth). It is older than any village or civilization can remember, and much of its origin is unknown. What is known is that it is immensely strong and sturdy, like the ground beneath your feet. With a durable body made out of ancient dripstone spikes, the &2Ancient Guardian &rhas strong defensive capabilities. These defenses help it when fighting its sworn enemy, the&b Cloud Golem. &rA battle between &2earth&r and &bsky,&2 ground&r and&b air, &ris quite the sight to behold."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Ancient Guardian is found in the Ancient Stronghold. Use an &6Eye of Many Ribs &rto locate it."
	]
	quest.2D66D75E2B6F03B7.title: "Witch Hut"
	quest.2D772D9BF5C91E17.quest_subtitle: "{components:{\"ftbquests:loot_crate\":\"iron\"},count:1,id:\"ftbquests:lootcrate\"}"
	quest.2D80F91B985C5AD6.title: "Lightning Dragonsteel Armor"
	quest.2D9A52BBBEDFA36F.quest_desc: [
		"&#6EC1FFSimple Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it blesses nearby creatures with Stone Ward."
		"Damage reduction grows stronger when unarmored."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
	]
	quest.2D9A52BBBEDFA36F.quest_subtitle: "Stand unbroken"
	quest.2DB09CD887C7E864.quest_desc: [
		"Great work! Here's a map to some other villages that we can help out. Additionally, if you'd like to visit a hub of commerce, here's a map to the Bazaar. "
		""
		"Many Villagers gather there so you may find some interesting Rumors there..."
	]
	quest.2DB09CD887C7E864.quest_subtitle: "Trade with Villagers and get rewards!"
	quest.2DB09CD887C7E864.title: "Trading with Villagers II"
	quest.2DB4F395EA26DF4B.quest_subtitle: "Find a Coliseum"
	quest.2DF0C8FC6724145A.title: "Jungles"
	quest.2E0301DAF9F23CC7.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.2E0301DAF9F23CC7.title: "Ancient Portal"
	quest.2E0E5EAE4EA8EF64.quest_desc: ["&b\"&6If you share our passion for archeology, I can give you a map to the digsite we are currently working on&r&b. Unfortunately, we don't make a lot of money so &6a couple of emeralds&r&b would go a long way to securing you that map and me more food!\""]
	quest.2E0E5EAE4EA8EF64.quest_subtitle: "An Offer from Nico"
	quest.2E0E5EAE4EA8EF64.title: "Buying: Archeology Site Map"
	quest.2E19F0BE4F093019.quest_subtitle: "Kill 1000 zombie"
	quest.2E19F0BE4F093019.title: "Earth Clean"
	quest.2E4E63A4CBC9F840.quest_subtitle: "Even better two side!"
	quest.2E5343E57127BFA5.title: "Archeology Catacombs"
	quest.2E648F8887B844FC.quest_desc: [
		"The Arcana Pylon uses stored Spirits to power magic."
		""
		"Totems normally create weak Echoes."
		"The pylon removes this limit."
		""
		"&6Elemental Spirits:&r"
		"Amplifies aura effects from runes and totems."
		""
		"&dArcane Spirits:&r"
		"Speeds up nearby Spirit Altars."
	]
	quest.2E648F8887B844FC.quest_subtitle: "Empower Totem Magic"
	quest.2EC6AD9C95609D1B.title: "Jungle"
	quest.2ED776C129833AEA.title: "Saplings store"
	quest.2EFC5DBD8122A0AE.quest_desc: ["Far below the surface lies a twisted network of chambers, where the air is thick with disease and shadow. Once a place of treatment, it now resembles a burial ground for forgotten rulers, its halls echoing with the whispers of those long lost. Only the brave (or the desperate) dare to tread these haunted corridors."]
	quest.2EFC5DBD8122A0AE.quest_subtitle: "Find a Plague Asylum"
	quest.2F15E92700FF3609.title: "Enchanting Tower"
	quest.2F474B69D274C2AD.quest_desc: [
		"Spirit Rites work through a Rite Locus."
		""
		"Simple rites create a Seeking Locus."
		"More complex rites create a Bound Locus that affects the world."
		""
		"Tainted Rock disrupts arcana."
		"When a locus travels over it, the rite will not activate."
		""
		"A Rite Anchor can redirect and modify a passing locus by defining its travel direction."
		""
		"Anchors stop working when powered by redstone."
		""
		"⸻"
		""
		"Locus Boons"
		"Modify a Bound Locus"
		""
		"A locus can gain Elemental Boons when passing over Rite Anchors."
		""
		"Limits:"
		"• Maximum 4 boons"
		"• Each boon works up to 2 times"
		""
		"Effects:"
		""
		"&#4BF3DA✧ Aerial&r"
		"Increases speed."
		""
		"&#1D64E8✧ Aqueous&r"
		"Increases potency."
		""
		"&#48EE19✧ Earthen&r"
		"Increases impact."
		""
		"&#FA9A1F✧ Infernal&r"
		"Increases distance."
		""
		"&#D546FF✧ Arcane&r"
		"Changes travel direction."
		""
		"&#CB0CF8✧ Eldritch&r"
		"Splits the locus into two copies."
		"Copies cannot split again."
		""
		"&#EE2C88✧ Sacred&r"
		"Restores lifespan over time."
		""
		"&#792CEC✧ Wicked&r"
		"Consumes an existing boon to instantly restore lifespan."
		""
		"Sacrifice order:"
		"Speed → Potency → Impact → Distance."
	]
	quest.2F474B69D274C2AD.quest_subtitle: "How Rite Locus Works"
	quest.2F474B69D274C2AD.title: "Locus Behavior"
	quest.2F657C8CD3860E08.quest_desc: [
		"A &bGeas&r is a semi-permanent soul pact."
		""
		"Geasa are created using the &bSoulbinding Brazier&r."
		""
		"Each pact requires:"
		"&8●&r A central item"
		"&8●&r Additional ingredients"
		"&8●&r Required arcana"
		""
		"Ignite the Brazier with Ether."
		"Interact with it to offer blood and seal the pact."
		""
		"Multiple players may bind at once."
		"Each soul can hold up to two active geasa."
		""
		"Geasa are powerful, but always come with drawbacks."
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&lForswearing a pact&r"
		""
		""
		"Assemble the same materials used to create the pact."
		""
		"Ignite the Brazier with &bParacausal Flame&r instead of Ether."
		""
		"This burns the contract away instead of binding it."
		""
		"The rest of the ritual works the same."
	]
	quest.2F657C8CD3860E08.quest_subtitle: "Binding a soul to a pact"
	quest.2F657C8CD3860E08.title: "Geas Magic"
	quest.2F65E61ADD2EDC17.quest_desc: ["Cheap cost at start to give access to spell without consume scroll."]
	quest.2F6BCEE3BBBE7ECE.quest_desc: [
		"As you gather the last of the materials to start the Ritual, a voice stops you."
		""
		"         &2  \"You Mustn't.\""
		"                &2          \"The Beast is\""
		"           &2     \"a Fierce Foe\""
		"                       &2           \"Mayhaps even\""
		"                &2  \"Stronger than\""
		"                           &2   \"The Heir of the End.\""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"    &2      \"Though.\""
		"          &2    \"If Thou could Slay it\""
		"         &2  \"Perhaps Thou\""
		"                              &2   \"Could even stop Those\""
		"&2\"Of the Dark Tower\""
	]
	quest.2F6BCEE3BBBE7ECE.title: "Chimeric Beast II"
	quest.2F7F649DE17C4C32.quest_subtitle: "Turn item into material"
	quest.2F933AD3B96685AE.title: "Magnolia Woodlands"
	quest.2F9EECF98AF13434.title: "Arctic"
	quest.2FDCD8AB6F6B08BE.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/xendah_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.2FED04E9F39720EA.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5Imbued weapon with explosive power!!!"
	quest.301C43ADA339B561.quest_subtitle: "Longer summoning"
	quest.3030D3181B98EDB3.quest_desc: [
		"A familiar devoted to sacred magic."
		"While primarily supportive, it can also unleash powerful holy spells."
		""
		"&9Abilities:&r"
		""
		"• Attacks undead creatures on sight."
		""
		"• If it encounters a Zombified Villager, it will attempt to cure them."
		""
		"&dCreation:&r"
		""
		"Cast the &eCleanse&r spell near an untamed Necromancer Familiar to transform it into a Cleric."
	]
