	quest.3307AAC44BB5758D.quest_subtitle: "Acknowledge no one, and be acknowledged by none"
	quest.332DE12A4A904DE3.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/darknix_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.33417DADB1C6E9A6.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5Once a &elegendary&r&l&n&5samurai's blade!"
	quest.3372926BDD3A709E.quest_desc: [
		"To summon a Drygmy, right click a &2Mossy cobblestone&r with &eDrygmy token&r, after a while the stone will turn into &2Drygmy henge&r and a Drygmy will appear. "
		""
		"A Drygmy will interact certain mobs to obtain their dropped items without killing them. To retrieve these items you will need place chests nearby the henge. Each action by a Drygmy will consume Source from a nearby &5Source Jar&r, if Source runs out then it will stop generating items."
	]
	quest.3372926BDD3A709E.title: "Mini god"
	quest.339FA351D4D2BDFD.quest_desc: ["The &6Cave Compendium is found in &eUnderground Cabins&r. Alternatively, the compendium can be crafted using a book, a gold nugget, and any cave tablet. It can be filled with entries about the new Alex's Caves biomes by deciphering cave tablets at a spelunkery table."]
	quest.339FA351D4D2BDFD.quest_subtitle: "Discover more about Alex's Caves"
	quest.339FA351D4D2BDFD.title: "Cave Compendium"
	quest.33C050328C9C732C.quest_desc: ["Incorporate an external storage, such as a chest into the refined storage setup."]
	quest.33E92208F61B1E3A.quest_subtitle: "Defensive capabilities when player falls below half health"
	quest.3408510E7D1AD32E.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.3408510E7D1AD32E.title: "Lab"
	quest.340AEA7194551724.quest_desc: [
		"Think the &3Adjudicator&r was difficult? His successor is even worse. More powerful than an evoker and adjudicator combined, this Illager leader lives within the &dPillager Fortress&r. Despite his great strengths, defeating just him is not the only hard part. He is protected by legions of marauders, vindicators, ravagers, and more. To get to the &eInvoker&r, one must be prepared. "
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The &eInvoker&r spawns at the top of the &dPillager Fortress&r."
	]
	quest.3424D529ADF53915.quest_desc: ["Augmenting table allow upgrade an item had affix at a high cost or reroll affix value."]
	quest.347630D4CCE688A4.quest_desc: [
		"The &cWithered Abomination&r is a pale imitation of its namesake. Created from a failed attempt by a blood mage to resurrect &bthe Wither&r, it shares some traits with its predecessor, but relies more on brute force rather than ranged attacks or explosions. It’s imposing appearance and hostile behavior is thought to be why it can now be found guarding some treasures of the &4Nether.&r Someone, possibly the very same blood mage who created the &cWithered Abomination,&r now uses it as a security guard."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Withered Abomination is found in the Withered Vault within the &4Nether.&r Use an &6Eye of Soul&r to locate it."
	]
	quest.34835E9F34DBF9EE.quest_desc: [
		"A &bTrowel&r randomly places blocks from your hotbar when used."
		""
		"An &bAbacus&r can be used to count the number of blocks between the block you right clicked and the block you are looking at, up to 48 blocks."
		""
		"A &bSawmill&r is similar to a stonecutter, but for processing wood instead of stone. Logs and planks can be input into the sawmill."
	]
	quest.34835E9F34DBF9EE.quest_subtitle: "Tools to aid in Building!"
	quest.34835E9F34DBF9EE.title: "Building Tools"
	quest.3492C7F03829A2A5.quest_desc: [
		"Import from an external inventory. "
		""
		"Note: By default, the top row indicates the blocklisted items. Can change to allowable items."
	]
	quest.34B1062817E19ECD.quest_desc: [
		"There are many &6Storage Upgrades&r that can improve capacity and add new functions."
		""
		"For example, the &6Stack Upgrade&r doubles the number of items that fit in a single slot."
		"Higher tiers can increase this even further."
		""
		"Check &6EMI&r to see all available upgrades."
		""
		"Be careful not to confuse &6Backpack Upgrades&r with &6Storage Upgrades&r."
	]
	quest.34B1062817E19ECD.quest_subtitle: "Expanding functionality"
	quest.34B1062817E19ECD.title: "Storage Upgrades"
	quest.34C3FF639C0ED7FC.quest_desc: ["Runewood is a strange mix of nature and magic, found often in open plains and sometimes in forests. Its orange-yellow leaves make it easy t"]
	quest.34C3FF639C0ED7FC.quest_subtitle: "Wood of Magic"
	quest.34C3FF639C0ED7FC.title: "Runewood"
