	quest.37CC92B7A18C2F7B.quest_subtitle: "Ol' Reliable"
	quest.37CC92B7A18C2F7B.title: "Netherite Armor"
	quest.37D76492A75AB495.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/xendah_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.37F7C8E9869CC663.title: "Fire Dragonsteel Armor"
	quest.385D04475177DDE9.quest_desc: [
		"The &4Lifestealer&r was once upon a time just an average guy. But misfortune struck and they became a victim of dark magic. Struck with a curse and turned into a creature that feeds off of the life force of others, the &4Lifestealer&r is a frightening, bloodthirsty sight. At first appearing to be a large hooded figure, the &4Lifestealer&r reveals its true form by screaming after either making an attack or receiving enough damage."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The &4Lifestealer&r can spawn under typical hostile mob spawning conditions, EXCEPT it is much more rare and it can only spawn after &6day 100&r"
	]
	quest.38635AA298CDC41C.quest_desc: [
		"&aPros:&r"
		"&8●&r Malignant Critical Strikes devour life essence"
		"&8●&r Devoured essence heals based on damage dealt"
		""
		"&4Cons:&r"
		"&8●&r Overusing the healing effect reduces incoming healing over time"
		""
		""
		"&8Pedestal Items:&r"
		"8x Living Flesh"
		"4x Imitation Flesh"
		""
		"&8Central Item:&r"
		"8x Malignant Pewter Plating"
		""
		"&8Spirits:&r"
		"32x &#EE2C88Sacred&r"
		"32x &#D546FFArcane&r"
		"32x &#CB0CF8Eldritch&r"
	]
	quest.38635AA298CDC41C.quest_subtitle: "Take the life of your enemies"
	quest.3882D7161BA896AE.quest_subtitle: "Obtain every unique weapon. Good luck..."
	quest.3882D7161BA896AE.title: "All Unique Weapons"
	quest.388DF8A8FEE142F7.title: "Snifferhenge"
	quest.38939111B9E46266.quest_subtitle: "Regular turtle shell, but now with knockback resistance"
	quest.38BF3AC7B84040E5.title: "Minka Village"
	quest.38E1D317D4EEA79C.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5Once a longsword of a legendary warrior that sadly fell ill"
	quest.393162735998BA87.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/banndu_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.39352B7CECAC84F4.quest_subtitle: "Let them cook"
	quest.39352B7CECAC84F4.title: "Master Chef"
	quest.394272D93F2FE569.quest_subtitle: "Deal 500.000 Damage"
	quest.39475684487F1958.quest_desc: [
		"Long ago, a blacksmith created a hammer that would never break. When an assassin came to steal it, the weapon bound to its maker’s soul reacted, pulling them both into the Nether."
		""
		"The assassin was erased, but a shard of the blacksmith’s soul endured, merging with stone, obsidian, and lava until it became the Netherite Monstrosity — a creature that remembers what it once was."
		""
		"Now it waits in the endless red gloom, far from the overworld. To reach it, you must use the Eye of Monstrous, an artifact that carries you to the place where this monster resides."
		"{image:kubejs:textures/quests/cataclysm/netherite_monstrosity.png width:100 height:100 align:center fit:true}"
	]
	quest.394E9F83FB77E302.quest_desc: [
		"Not much is known about the &6Echo of Tyros&r, save that he was once a legendary pyromancer known as the &cFirst Flamebearer&r. In life, Tyros sought absolute mastery over fire, believing flame to be the purest expression of magic. When his mortal form finally failed, his will burned on, leaving behind a powerful echo bound eternally to the inferno he created. His rage and magic still linger, testing any who dare challenge the legacy of flame."
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		""
		"The &6Echo of Tyros&r dwells within the &cHellfire Citadel&r, a scorched stronghold hidden deep within the world. To awaken him, one must reach the Citadel’s summit and use a &6Cinderous Soulcaller&r upon the ritual platform. Only those prepared to endure fire itself may hope to silence Tyros’ echo and claim the rewards left behind by the first master of flame."
	]
	quest.39E27D08343CC1EA.quest_desc: [
		"The &dWilden Chimera&r is a beast so powerful that it took the greatest wizards all of their power to trap it in an &5Archmage Tower&r. The tower by itself could not hold this creature, and many wizards had to stay behind to contain it. Overtime, they too became dark and corrupted. Be sure to train and grow in your power, for this tower is a deadly trap to those who go in unprepared. "
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The &dWilden Chimera&r can also be summoned with a &6Tablet of Summon Wilden&r. Only when augmented with a Wilden Spike, Wilden Horn, and a Wilden Wing, will this ritual summon the &dWilden Chimera&r. "
		""
		"&7NOTE: If summoning the chimera, this ritual will destroy blocks around the brazier."
	]
	quest.39E6836317A32051.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/alubisin_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.3A3F1E29C4C544EC.quest_desc: ["Priority to utilities, this is near endgame set for boss but true endgame set for adventure."]
	quest.3A816B96A7A7A38D.quest_subtitle: "This table can upgrade gem by using gem dust and forging material"
	quest.3A9E2ECAB0556728.quest_subtitle: "So.. you've found the Labyrinth. Do you dare to take on what's inside?"
	quest.3AB449E4D0F66E34.quest_desc: ["&5Source Stone&r can be use to craft &5Enchanting apparatus&r and &5Arcane core&r among other things."]
	quest.3AB449E4D0F66E34.title: "Mana Stone"
	quest.3AC5ABAB78D4A226.quest_desc: ["A big upgrade about armor and tool, strong protection against dragon, monster in overworld will no longer a problem to you. Each element type will have a diffirent strength, pick wisely"]
	quest.3AC5ABAB78D4A226.title: "Heavy armor"
	quest.3ACFD2EF49451E95.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Shrinkinator&r is a workstation used to shrink items for familiars."
		""
		"Players can also shrink food."
		"Shrunken food can be given to familiars to restore their health."
		""
		"Other items can be shrunk as well, including certain consumables."
		""
		"The &6Shrinkinator&r supports automation and can interact with hoppers."
	]
	quest.3ACFD2EF49451E95.quest_subtitle: "Item shrinking workstation"
	quest.3ADBC1D66AD8811A.quest_desc: ["There are many types of &5Source Relay&r. They act as as mana transfer devices. Using the &5Dominion Wand&r, Source may be transferred to &5Source Jar&r."]
	quest.3ADBC1D66AD8811A.title: "Mana Transfer"
	quest.3AF8B4EBCE54E817.title: "Archwood Forest"
	quest.3B1965C5BE57D7F6.quest_desc: [
		"Long ago, a dark order called the &5Abyss Callers&r tried to bind a mighty prehistoric creature through forbidden necromancy. The ritual failed—the beast’s soul turned on them, erasing their entire order."
		""
		"Defeated only by the &9first king&r and his circle of sorcerers, the creature’s body was sealed away, too powerful to destroy. Its &8dark energy&r still leaks from the depths, cursing all who wander close."
		""
		"Some say the &eEye of the Desert&r still points to its resting place. Will you end its curse… or join the bones beneath the sand?"
	]
	quest.3B2840F80C601A0F.quest_desc: [
		"&9The Leviathan&r was once the great deity of the ocean but is now contained inside an altar. This kraken-like creature dwells within the &9Sunken City&r and is guarded by the ocean coming to life. Giant masses of coral and merfolk reside within this city, ready to stop anyone who comes to try and take away their god. It’s not just the guards to watch out for, the &9Leviathan&r can defend itself quite well once awakened. But should you prevail, the ocean will bend to your will. "
		""
		"&7There is a rumor that eating the meat of&r &dmystical crabs&r &7can help ward you from the devastating effects of the Leviathan's attacks. But where can these crabs be found? And how does the crab meat gain its &r&dprotective powers?&r"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"To summon the Leviathan, place an Abyssal Sacrifice in the Altar of Abyss. This must be crafted using mob drops from those within the Sunken City. Use an &6Eye of Abyss&r to locate the Sunken City in the &2Overworld&r."
		""
		"&7HINT: The Leviathan can heal with Ender powers. It might be best to use a different school of magic for this fight."
	]
	quest.3B2DA52A95E1B730.title: "Bamboo Jungle"
	quest.3B42FA3380FA1610.title: "Swamp"
	quest.3B439C9F17E93522.title: "Silver Birch Forest"
	quest.3BA21B990625F684.quest_desc: [
		"&aPros:&r"
		"&8●&r Dealing ranged damage increases draw speed"
		""
		"&4Cons:&r"
		"&8●&r Missing a shot removes draw speed bonuses and slows draw speed"
