	quest.486D460A66203A95.quest_subtitle: "To be full is to be anchored"
	quest.4872C571502FFB48.title: "Pillager Outpost"
	quest.487E679F69B609B1.quest_desc: ["Spawn 8 flowers by hitting flowers with &6Pollen Puff&r."]
	quest.48A8BDBA503F6840.quest_desc: [
		"&bRawwrh!&r"
		""
		"Dragons have 5 stages. The ones on the surface are stages 2 and 3. The ones underground are stages 4 and 5. The bigger the dragon, the higher the stage and more difficult the fight. They have been placed under Tier 3 in the Boss Codex since that is middle-of-the-road."
		""
		"&7TIP: Dragon Eggs only drop from stage 4 and 5 &efemale&7 dragons."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Ice Dragons can be found in cold biomes such as snowy plains and ice spikes."
	]
	quest.48BDA991D14A345C.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Copper Backtank&r must be filled with air pressure to function."
		""
		"Place it down and connect a rotating shaft to the top to pressurize it."
		""
		"&eDiving Helmet&r"
		"When paired with a filled &6Copper Backtank&r, the helmet grants Water Breathing and Aqua Affinity."
		""
		"&eDiving Boots&r"
		"Cause the wearer to sink and disable swimming, allowing walking and jumping underwater."
		""
		"They also grant immunity to &6Mechanical Belts&r, &6Escalators&r, and &6Walkways&r."
	]
	quest.48BDA991D14A345C.quest_subtitle: "Diving equipment"
	quest.48D544814E5FE368.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/muba_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.48E3C2D33EFD6812.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5Elemental &eblade!&r"
	quest.493AC092DA35B1E1.title: "Jagged Peaks"
	quest.495CC7C5A8BEF15A.title: "Health Increase"
	quest.49F429157D62C2DC.quest_subtitle: "Water breathing and protection against frozen waters"
	quest.49F429157D62C2DC.title: "Three-Bolt Diving Suit"
	quest.49FB61DAB65D2BEF.quest_desc: ["Learn how to tame, train, and maim the various new mobs in this world in the upcoming Animal Trainer chapter."]
	quest.4A18B3B814D57B69.quest_desc: [
		"&bFrostmaws&r are dangerous beasts found rarely in snowy areas. Their massive size, impressive speed, and powerful ice breath make them near-impossible opponents. If, on your travels, you encounter one sleeping in your path, it's likely best to take a different route and let it lay. The beast guards a precious ice crystal that can unleash pure winter energy when wielded."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Use the &6Eye of Frost&r to locate the &bFrostmaw &rin its snowy den."
	]
	quest.4A1D180F1688C261.title: "Ocean Monument"
	quest.4A4C7DC41D551FED.title: "Dry Brushland"
	quest.4A72D1BC57E0B869.quest_desc: [
		"Those who fled the Ender Dragon built the &7End Citadel&r, a fortress full of traps. Over time, the &0Void&r consumed the defenders, twisting them into &5Ender Golems&r."
		""
		"They no longer remember life, acting only to guard the citadel. The king of these lost warriors became the &5Ender Guardian&r. Perhaps a hero can free them from this cursed fate, but to see the truth, you will need the &dEye of Void&r."
	]
	quest.4A75FF97FF645E27.title: "Frostmaw Spawn"
	quest.4A958BA4CE4F0F17.quest_desc: [
		"&bRune Of Stone Ward&r grants small damage reduction."
		""
		"The effect grows stronger when unarmored."
	]
	quest.4A958BA4CE4F0F17.quest_subtitle: "Scaling damage reduction"
	quest.4AC60D7FD95B7758.quest_desc: [
		"Start pick your classes and progress through step by step until you reach true strength for an easier gameplay or feel free to skip this page and do whatever you think is best. "
