	quest.4B8615C5A1C38178.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5Little brother of emberlash!"
	quest.4B984DCF229D3525.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/molluto_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.4BC39CDB1DACC203.quest_subtitle: "{components:{\"ftbquests:loot_crate\":\"relics_cataclysm\"},count:1,id:\"ftbquests:lootcrate\"}"
	quest.4BEA1A6EE374A42E.quest_desc: [
		"Both machines can be fed a &6Cake o’ Enchanting&r to activate &eSuper Enchanting Mode&r."
		""
		"&eSuper Enchanting Mode&r"
		"Raises the enchantment level cap to 60 and enables Treasured Enchantments."
		""
		"In this mode the machines only accept &6Super Enchanting Templates&r."
		""
		"Place a block on top of the machine and a Lightning Rod nearby."
		"Super Enchanting Mode attracts lightning strikes."
		""
		"&eBlaze Forger bonuses&r"
		"While in Super Enchanting Mode, enchantments can exceed vanilla limits and even normally conflicting enchantments can be merged."
	]
	quest.4C0BA7F1453A9EA8.quest_desc: ["Residing within dark caves, the &4Mother of Spiders&r protects her kin. She is the last true descendant of &6Arachne&r and as such holds more power and abilities to the other arachnids you have encountered. The &4Mother&r poisons and slows her victims. She will also summon her children to help fight off attackers. Once defeated, she will leave behind a mess of her webs, and should you be lucky enough, one of her &cMandibles&r."]
	quest.4C21428819E5C7AC.quest_desc: ["This table is &d&lessential to casting spells.&r It enables one-time use spells to be added to spell books, allowing unlimited casts. Likewise, it may be used to remove spells from spellbooks. "]
	quest.4C3CD36614615318.quest_desc: ["Someone brought a Void Blossom into this world, where it absorbed local energy and became a terrifying predator. Its hard, dry shell can poison deeply, and it can even move through the ground like water. Yet it is still a plant—perhaps a little fire will finish the job."]
	quest.4C430AD8ACBEBF9E.quest_desc: [
		"&5&lCurseForge Page&r&r: https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/modpacks/integrated-minecraft"
		""
		"&5&lDiscord&r&r: https://discord.gg/uMyJYrPy7x"
		""
		"&5&lYoutube&r&r: https://www.youtube.com/@craisinlord"
	]
	quest.4C430AD8ACBEBF9E.quest_subtitle: "Website and Discord Links"
	quest.4C62E1FCAC7A1A57.quest_desc: [
		"&#6EC1FFSimple Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it increases block interaction range and item pickup distance."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
	]
	quest.4C62E1FCAC7A1A57.quest_subtitle: "Extend reach"
	quest.4C62EC461F0340AC.quest_desc: [
		"As you deliver the last of the materials to the Witch, they appear slightly shocked."
		""
		"&b\"Perfect work! Honestly, you did that much faster than I thought you would.\""
		""
		"&b\"I was going to say,&d「Don't forget your actions reflect on me, your referrer」&r&b, but you are more than talented enough. Go be my representative.\"&r"
		""
		"&b\"I don't care very much for them, so you taking my place is perfect.\"&r"
	]
	quest.4C62EC461F0340AC.quest_subtitle: "Gather the required materials to gain the map to the Apothecaries Abode"
	quest.4C62EC461F0340AC.title: "The Witch's Request"
	quest.4C6C1CD4824BB8E7.quest_desc: [
		"&6Limited Barrels&r come in four variants: I, II, III, and IV."
		"Each tier increases the number of items the barrel can store."
		""
		"They function similarly to drawers, holding large quantities of a single item."
		""
		"&8● &6Interaction&r"
		"Right-click — Deposit items"
		"Double right-click — Deposit all matching items from inventory"
		"Left-click — Take one item"
		"Shift + Left-click — Take one stack"
		""
		"&8● &6Filtering&r"
		"Limited Barrels can also act as filters."
		""
		"Use the &6Storage Tool&r in Locking mode and right-click the barrel to apply a lock."
		"Then place an item inside. The barrel will only accept that item, even if emptied."
		""
		"You can also enable filtering through the barrel settings."
		"Open the settings, go to slot memory, and memorize the slot."
		""
		"Both methods allow the barrel to store items while acting as a filter."
	]
	quest.4C6C1CD4824BB8E7.quest_subtitle: "High-capacity storage"
	quest.4C6C1CD4824BB8E7.title: "Limited Barrels"
	quest.4C840076783D73B9.quest_desc: [
		"Since you're here, you probably understand the basics of the &dQuest Book&r. However, in case you are new to this, here's some important things to keep in mind:"
		""
		"- The &btab/menu&r on the left (indicated by the &cred arrow&r) shows all of the &eChapters&r within the &dQuest Book&r. You can keep the tab open by clicking the pin in the top right of the tab."
		""
		"- L-Click on a quest to open up each individual &equest page&r. The &6top left&r shows what you need to do. You can click on items to view recipes and/or submit items. The &6top right&r shows what you will get as a reward. Be sure to click it in order to collect it. The &6bottom middle&r (what you are looking at currently) is the description. This can include lore, hints, information, and more to help you complete the quest."
		""
		"- Some quests have more than one page. Either use your &5scroll wheel&r or &5click the arrow&r at the bottom right of the &equest page&r to go to the next page. &bTry it now!&r"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"- &eSome chapters and many quests&r are &binitially hidden&r, until they are triggered by &bcertain events&r. This is usually by completing a previous quest or finding a specific item."
		""
		"- One chapter acts as a storage for &dhidden recipes&r, unlocked by finding &7Tattered Books&r. Claim your reward on the top right of this quest box to unlock your &bfirst secret recipe&r!"
	]
	quest.4C840076783D73B9.quest_subtitle: "Learn how the Quest Book works!"
	quest.4C840076783D73B9.title: "Quests"
	quest.4CA94FAA40ECF71D.quest_desc: ["In a heated basin, mix together copper and zinc. Place the basin on top of a blaze burner. R-click the blaze burner with fuel (coal, wood, blaze rod, etc.) to heat."]
	quest.4CA94FAA40ECF71D.title: "Brass Casings and Ingots"
	quest.4CAF984AB7164AAA.quest_desc: [
		"&bRune Of Burning Fervor&r grants Burning Fervor at half strength."
		""
		"Increases attack speed and mining speed slightly."
	]
	quest.4CAF984AB7164AAA.quest_subtitle: "Slight speed boost"
	quest.4D3C5034A65FECBE.quest_subtitle: "End dimension version of netherite. Better armor toughness and knockback resistance"
	quest.4D3C5034A65FECBE.title: "Aeternium Armor"
	quest.4D456BBE114AE0E5.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.4D456BBE114AE0E5.title: "Deathworm Pit"
	quest.4D74B46861B7E82C.quest_desc: ["&bRune Of Twinned Duration&r extends the duration of beneficial effects."]
	quest.4D74B46861B7E82C.quest_subtitle: "Longer positive effects"
	quest.4DC724CF48C67624.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/gusnow_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.4DCEED6B3ADC1CB9.title: "Sunken City"
	quest.4DF026D1B98BB152.title: "Nether Jungle"
	quest.4E141AEEA3889F77.quest_desc: ["Now you are eligible to craft the &5Archmage spell book&r, this is the highest-tier book and allow you to cast all existing glyphs."]
	quest.4E141AEEA3889F77.quest_subtitle: "ban this item"
	quest.4E141AEEA3889F77.title: "Dumbledore"
	quest.4E4052F7EAD4FDD6.quest_desc: ["Bright banners and painted walls lure travelers closer, but inside these towering strongholds, chaos reigns. Each floor brims with bandits and traps, their laughter echoing as waves of foes pour from endless spawners. Conquer the towers, and their riches—and notoriety—are yours."]
	quest.4E4052F7EAD4FDD6.quest_subtitle: "Find the Bandit Towers"
	quest.4EABBF55DD327D1C.quest_desc: ["Look like a true warrior, not only that this set will increase your dmg. "]
	quest.4EABBF55DD327D1C.title: "Ironshade"
	quest.4ED25F904208FCC1.quest_desc: [
		"Progression in this pack is &lopen&r and &lflexible.&r While doing one thing, you’ll often stumble upon something new."
		""
		"Start by finding shelter and making yourself a home. As you explore, you’ll discover things that catch your attention—then check the questbook to learn more. Maybe it’s part of a magic path, or leads to something greater."
		""
		"You can also use the recipe viewer (EMI): press &lR&r in your inventory to see how an item is made, or &lU&r to see what it’s used for."
	]
	quest.4ED25F904208FCC1.quest_subtitle: "Your Own Path"
	quest.4ED25F904208FCC1.title: "Progression"
	quest.4EDB4DAF0FA995ED.quest_desc: [
		"As you read the journal, a traveller taps your shoulder."
		""
		"She clears her throat and speaks urgently, &b\"Hey there, friend. I see you've found my journal.\"&r You try to apologize for snooping but she cuts you off. "
		""
		"&b\"Oh don't worry, I need help anyways. I’ve tried tempting that blasted bear with honey, but the creature’s got a mean streak that sugar can’t melt. Do you have any ideas?\"&r "
	]
	quest.4EDB4DAF0FA995ED.quest_subtitle: "You stumble upon the Bearclaw Inn"
	quest.4EDB4DAF0FA995ED.title: "The Bearclaw Inn"
	quest.4EF2E6568A268915.title: "Desert"
	quest.4F0680DE5FA4F35A.title: "Blackstone Basin"
	quest.4F10A6E40DCC221D.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/molluto_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.4F15930FFB341E4F.quest_desc: ["By making first tier spell book you will able to cast tier 1 glyphs you learned, to make glyphs put the spell book on main hand and right click the &5Scribe's table&r then pick a glyphs you need, after that toss item require appear on the table and glyphs will be done. Remember to check key bind for spell book on settings to use and cast spell."]
	quest.4F15930FFB341E4F.title: "Start With Read"
	quest.4F17BB5910E59ECB.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/pangolin_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.4F4C049182694CC7.title: "Fungal Fens"
	quest.4FB1EB89EB09F3F4.quest_desc: [
		"&#1E5AA8Advanced Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it weaves a Bound Rite Locus."
		"Blocks touched by the Locus are pulled downward."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
		"[&#CB0CF8✧&r] &#CB0CF8Eldritch&r"
	]
	quest.4FB1EB89EB09F3F4.quest_subtitle: "Impose weight"
	quest.4FE4A83E25720B57.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/drazor_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.4FE6E91078023593.title: "Burning Arena"
	quest.508D8075984EBD02.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5A weapon blessed by the gods!"
	quest.508F651458C4E4F5.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Arcane Anvil&r is used to improve spells."
		""
		"Place a Spell Scroll and an &bInk&r of the same rarity to level it up."
		""
		"You can also bind spells to weapons."
		""
		"Place a weapon and a Spell Scroll in the &6Arcane Anvil&r."
		"The scroll is consumed and the weapon gains the ability to cast that spell."
	]
	quest.508F651458C4E4F5.quest_subtitle: "Upgrade Spells"
	quest.509E9CA83FBC780E.quest_subtitle: "Find a Fishing Hut"
	quest.50AC14CB91DC5C15.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Elevator Pulley&r is used to create moving elevators. "
		""
		"For a full explanation, check the &6Ponder&r scene &8(hold W)&r."
	]
	quest.50AC14CB91DC5C15.quest_subtitle: "Vertical transport"
	quest.50BFC79A5F49A376.quest_subtitle: "You are da BOMB!"
	quest.50BFC79A5F49A376.title: "Da Bomb"
	quest.50D5B1A83B9D874F.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5A axe drenched the soul of the dead!"
	quest.50F2F6ABC40E7424.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/zatlah_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.50F6FA24B2FDB42E.quest_desc: [
		"You see a bottle with a letter inside of it floating among the waves. Curious, you grab it and fish out the letter inside. It reads"
		""
		"&b「Calling all fishing enthusists. Come to the Fisherman's Lodge to meet other Fishermen, discuss fishing strategies, and find other like minded folk. We hoped this letter hooked your interest and that we can reel you in!」&r"
	]
	quest.50F6FA24B2FDB42E.quest_subtitle: "You see a bottle with a letter inside floating among the waves..."
	quest.50F6FA24B2FDB42E.title: "A Bottle among the Waves"
	quest.50FAEEFED34333DE.title: "Ruined Citadel"
	quest.50FECB5087B9E8B1.quest_desc: ["Inventory cables are great for connecting your inventory network together across lots of empty space. There are different types of cables as well. Framed cables can be painted to fit in with surrounding blcoks."]
	quest.50FECB5087B9E8B1.title: "Inventory Cables"
	quest.5100CFAD43E7D67A.quest_desc: ["Rising like a monument to conquest, this sprawling fortress serves as a bastion of Illager power. Its many levels are patrolled by raiders and spellcasters, their banners declaring dominion over the land. Within its halls lie chambers of wealth, guarded by Evokers whose magic is as deadly as their stares."]
	quest.5100CFAD43E7D67A.quest_subtitle: "Find an Illager Fort"
	quest.51040727BD2ABC19.quest_desc: [
		"“You are what you eat.” This saying has perhaps never been more apt than when it comes to a &cCrimson Mosquito&r. The mosquito will transform into a &3Warped Mosco&r by drinking the blood of a Warped Fungus &dMungus&r. Once the transformation is complete, the &3Mosco&r will become enraged and attack any nearby creature it sees as food, using its massive body as a weapon. It is unknown why only the &dMungus&r seems to cause this reaction. Perhaps this should be studied more…"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&dMungus&r spawn in &dMushroom Island&r biomes, and &cCrimson Mosquitos&r spawn in &cCrimson Forest&r biomes. A fly can also turn into a Crimson Mosquito if exposed to the Nether for too long. You will need to get these two mobs in the same place. You can r-click a &dMungus&r with &3warped fungus&r to make it a &3Warped Fungus &r&dMungus&r, but only if it does not already have mushrooms of a different type on its body."
	]
	quest.511B4251A6FE1258.quest_desc: [
		"Tired of having overflowing chests? Worry no more with the super advanced (but somehow still simple?) &6storage terminal&r! When placed on a network with an inventory connecter, you can store as much as you want within that inventory network. No need to worry about sorting either. This machine comes with a built in search tool."
		""
		"&6This is a great device to access your vaults. Thousands of items within easy reach!&r"
		""
		"&bNOTE: Needs an inventory connecter to access multiple vaults at once."
	]
	quest.511B4251A6FE1258.quest_subtitle: "Tom's Simple Storage"
	quest.511B4251A6FE1258.title: "Storage Made Simple"
	quest.512E3BB9064CEEC3.title: "Icy Heights"
	quest.514A3B3B7CC903B7.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/zatlah_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.5157AE29DAEBB0A1.title: "Dark Metal Armor"
	quest.516DF3AB5A9E93AC.quest_desc: ["If you have any questions, please feel free to ask on discord! &dCraisin&r or &eLeafyyy&r are usually around to answer questions. Make sure to check that your question hasn't already been answered, though."]
	quest.517D9D523E695937.quest_desc: ["The main component for a Refined Storage setup. To power, use the &eAlternator&r and associated &eConnector&r setup. Note that bigger setups attached to a controller will require more power. "]
	quest.517D9D523E695937.quest_subtitle: "Nvidia or AMD?"
	quest.51C5A13E468075F6.title: "Obsidilith Arena"
	quest.51D9307FA7FEDA46.title: "Mangrove Swamp"
	quest.51DA55FEB55D644A.quest_desc: ["Without eyes to see with, the &3Warden&r uses preternatural hearing to locate trespassers in its &3Ancient City&r. This being usually remains submerged in the skulk, but it will appear should the alarm sound three times. Are you brave enough to explore the &3Ancient City&r and seek out its treasures?"]
	quest.51DCF05D37DCFC0D.title: "Mushroom House"
	quest.522E5672D2B41A32.quest_desc: ["More slot, more mana is needed."]
	quest.5230D3587B041C15.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Rotation Speed Controller&r allows precise control of rotational speed."
		""
		"It must be paired with a &6Large Cogwheel&r to function."
		""
		"When the cogwheel powers the controller, it outputs a custom speed through its sides."
		"It can also adjust the speed of a connected Large Cogwheel."
		""
		"&eConfiguration&r"
		"Use the value settings panel on the front or back to set RPM and rotation direction."
		""
		"Maximum speed is 256 RPM."
	]
	quest.5230D3587B041C15.quest_subtitle: "Speed control"
	quest.52624498675F3C66.quest_desc: [
		"&aPros:&r"
		"&8●&r Enter stasis when struck"
		"&8●&r Potion effects are paused during stasis"
		"&8●&r Effects that do not rely on time remain active"
		""
		"&4Cons:&r"
		"&8●&r Incoming healing is reduced to one quarter"
		""
		""
		"&8Pedestal Items:&r"
		"16x Malignant Pewter Plating"
		"16x Imitation Flesh"
		"16x Void Salts"
		""
		"&8Center Item:&r"
		"Fused Consciousness"
		""
		"&8Spirits:&r"
		"32x &#EE2C88Sacred&r"
		"32x &#792CECWicked&r"
		"32x &#D546FFArcane&r"
		"32x &#CB0CF8Eldritch&r"
		"32x &#4BF3DAAerial&r"
		"32x &#1D64E8Aqueous&r"
		"32x &#48EE19Earthen&r"
		"32x &#FA9A1FInfernal&r"
	]
	quest.52624498675F3C66.quest_subtitle: "Take it all, let it never stop, more, and more, and more"
	quest.5266F98480DF659C.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5&cBerserker's dream?&e"
	quest.526BC7C6C60EA979.quest_desc: ["Can't have you dying on me so easily. Here, I'll cut you a deal. You survive long enough and I'll give you rewards."]
	quest.526BC7C6C60EA979.quest_subtitle: "Survive and get rewarded!"
	quest.526BC7C6C60EA979.title: "Survival Skills I"
	quest.52A04EC4A470E01D.title: "Flower Forest"
	quest.52A6C27732915801.title: "Knifes"
	quest.52C9EED9E31E0821.quest_desc: [
		"Long ago, before players or villagers or even creepers, dinosaurs called the Overworld their home. But disaster struck, and they were forced to flee deep underground into &aPrimordial Caves&r. Only one species, the &6Thornapod&r, remained on the surface, and that would become its downfall."
		""
		"Archeologists throughout the realm speak of the &eAncient Remnant&r. It is a skeletal statue resembling a &6Thornapod&r that can be found at the bottom of the &eCursed Pyramid&r, a vast new dungeon within the desert. The &ePyramid&r is full of treasures galore, but that is not all that lies inside. Traps, hostiles, and puzzles await the player to stop them from conquering this dungeon."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"When you find the Ancient Remnant, it will be stationary like a statue. You’ll need to right-click it with the &eNecklace of the Desert&r. The Necklace is hidden within suspicious sand in the Cursed Pyramid. Use the &6Eye of Desert&r to locate the Cursed Pyramid."
	]
	quest.53064706B9E4D8B2.quest_desc: [
		"A swift familiar specialized in ranged combat and scouting."
		""
		"&9Abilities:&r"
		""
		"• Protects the owner from enemies aiming at them, even if they are unseen."
		""
		"• Can track creatures that drop a specific item when shown that item."
		""
		"&dHabitat:&r"
		""
		"Often found hunting prey within &2forests.&r"
	]
	quest.53064706B9E4D8B2.quest_subtitle: "Silent Tracker"
	quest.53064706B9E4D8B2.title: "Hunter"
	quest.53097A671A7CCBD9.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5The weapon born in the void!"
	quest.530ED09D40063243.title: "Winter Wagon"
	quest.53326FE43A0BC420.quest_subtitle: "Increases health and saturation from consuming raw meat"
	quest.535D6158419D6F4A.quest_desc: [
		"Within the &5Apothecary Abode&r, you discover a note detailing the creation of both &bEnchanted Golden Apples&r and &bEnchantned Totems of Undying&r. It contains coordinates, as it was originally intended to be sent."
		""
		"It appears to be addressed to the leader of the Illagers. "
	]
	quest.535D6158419D6F4A.quest_subtitle: "You find a note addressed to a mansion..."
	quest.535D6158419D6F4A.title: "The Illager Institution"
	quest.537502D17BEAA19F.quest_desc: ["&bDiamond Armor&r can be upgraded 3 different ways, each with thier own perks."]
	quest.537502D17BEAA19F.title: "Diamond Armor"
	quest.5384F4B3040CFB54.quest_desc: [
		"The &bSympathy Drive&r combines &#792CECWicked&r and &#EE2C88Sacred&r energy."
		""
		"When the Crucible’s Impetus takes damage, Wicked charge stores it."
		""
		"When healed by the &bMending Diffuser&r, Sacred charge restores extra durability."
		""
		"The boost lasts for three cycles."
	]
	quest.5384F4B3040CFB54.quest_subtitle: "Harness opposing forces"
	quest.539896EACCF3F1AC.quest_desc: [
		"&bHallowed Gold&r is gold infused with Sacred arcana."
		""
		"It conducts spirit energy more efficiently than normal gold."
		""
		"Used as a base for altars, braziers, and arcane devices."
		""
		"Opens the path to &6Source Magic&r."
	]
	quest.539896EACCF3F1AC.quest_subtitle: "Refined arcane conductor"
	quest.53A435B234BE2374.quest_desc: [
		"&aPros:&r"
		"&8●&r Increases Soul Ward capacity"
		"&8●&r Increases Soul Ward integrity"
		""
		"&4Cons:&r"
		"&8●&r Halves Soul Ward recovery rate"
		""
		""
		"&8Pedestal Items:&r"
		"8x Refined Soulstone"
		""
		"&8Central Item:&r"
		"12x Soul Stained Steel Plating"
		""
		"&8Spirits:&r"
		"16x &#D546FFArcane&r"
		"16x &#48EE19Earthen&r"
	]
	quest.53A435B234BE2374.quest_subtitle: "Be strong when you are needed"
	quest.53AF2B722A69DCDC.quest_desc: ["Tucked away in the tall grass, this lonely house stands weathered and broken, its timbers groaning with age. Easy to overlook, it bears little more than the memory of those who once called it home. Still, even the smallest refuge can hold a story."]
	quest.53AF2B722A69DCDC.quest_subtitle: "Find a Small Prairie House"
	quest.53BD475217957F3B.quest_desc: [
		"&e\"Regions Unexplored\"&r adds many biomes, including some with their own types of &bdirt&r. While there is an option to limit biome generation to only include default dirt, in order to allow for greater customization, this is not enabled by default."
		""
		"However, to ease inventory management issues, all new dirt types can be converted to vanilla &bdirt&r through the &bCrafting Table&r. Try it out!"
		""
		"Many can also be crafted through custom recipes (mostly involving their respective saplings)."
	]
	quest.53BD475217957F3B.quest_subtitle: "Easy Conversions for Inventory Management!"
	quest.53D7E09EFF7E8F03.quest_desc: [
		"&bRune Of Heresy&r silences enemy spirit magic."
		""
		"Effect stacks up to full suppression."
	]
	quest.53D7E09EFF7E8F03.quest_subtitle: "Silence magic"
	quest.53DB7D6D3CCC5714.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/alubisin_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.53FCCDB2ABB362AA.quest_desc: ["Shoot 32 &eBee Stingers&r from a bow or crossbow."]
	quest.5407948AD7A6849A.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/spider_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.540D9116B5DD6109.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/buho_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.5419A340445822E5.title: "Outback"
	quest.541BBC35DA4F0B73.quest_desc: ["Sprouting from a cluster of towering fungi, this outpost of miners has carved their livelihood into the surface world. Ruthless and territorial, they will defend their claim with tooth and nail. Whether the giant mushrooms shield them from the sun or serve some darker purpose, none can say. One truth remains certain: the mine runs rich with ore, for those bold enough to claim it."]
	quest.541BBC35DA4F0B73.quest_subtitle: "Find a Mushroom Mine"
	quest.541CBFA78CCA3C1D.title: "Redstone Cavern"
	quest.544CD36D12C92902.quest_desc: [
		"Lost underground many years ago, these heavily armored knights are not men nor are they statues. Are they guarding something? They have forgotten what. Are they waiting for something? They have forgotten when. Are they mourning someone? They have forgotten whom. All they know is to slay those who approach their chambers. The armor is well made and keeps the knight protected. There is only one way to damage a &cFerrous Wroughtnaut&r; its weakness is for you to discover."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"You can find the &cFerrous Wroughtnaut&r by locating the entrance to &5The End&r."
	]
	quest.546301E7661AA511.quest_desc: [
		"These magical clothes have many upgraded variants. Tier upgrades can be achieved by placing 2 &6blaze rod&r on &5Arcane pedestal&r and armor on &5Enchanting apparatus&r. Moreover, you can add thread upgrades to your armor which will fit in tier I, II or III slots"
		""
		"Due to the magic flowing inside this equipment, it will slowly repair itself by consuming mana. "
	]
	quest.546301E7661AA511.quest_subtitle: "Basic clothes from ars"
	quest.546301E7661AA511.title: "Magical Armor"
	quest.5475E53B925BC09F.quest_subtitle: "Protection against acid and the irradiated effect"
	quest.5475E53B925BC09F.title: "Hazmat Suit"
	quest.548CA2477332624C.quest_subtitle: "Knockback resistance and strong protection"
	quest.548CA2477332624C.title: "Bone Reptile Armor"
	quest.54CA93112FAAE662.title: "Shrublands"
	quest.54FF59942B85CC4D.title: "Dunes"
	quest.5501173723FBA43B.quest_subtitle: "Trade with villager 500 times"
	quest.5501173723FBA43B.title: "Master of persuasion"
	quest.552D8109F40973DC.title: "Black Ice Glaciers"
	quest.55535225BDBDF6FD.quest_desc: [
		"Hell-themed meals can grant fire immunity or even turn fire into a beneficial effect."
		""
		"A &6Nether Stove&r should be a centerpiece of your kitchen."
	]
	quest.55535225BDBDF6FD.quest_subtitle: "Nether cooking"
	quest.55709EBAD751F02D.quest_subtitle: "Orbital Void ability. Eldritch and Ender school bonuses"
	quest.55709EBAD751F02D.title: "Abyssal Hide Armor"
	quest.55874DC6452BEA70.quest_desc: [
		"&6Mechanical Crafters&r automate crafting recipes."
		"Some recipes require them, such as &6Crushing Wheels&r."
		""
		""
		"&eCrafting layout&r"
		"Each crafter has an arrow showing where items are passed during crafting."
		""
		"Use a &6Wrench&r on the front to change the arrow direction."
		"All arrows must eventually converge on the same crafter to complete the recipe."
		""
		"&eItem input&r"
		"Items can be inserted manually or automatically using &6Funnels&r or &6Hoppers&r."
		""
		"&eInventory linking&r"
		"Use a &6Wrench&r on the sides or back of two adjacent crafters to link or unlink their inventories."
		""
		"Linked crafters can share items even if they are not part of the same recipe."
	]
	quest.55874DC6452BEA70.quest_subtitle: "Automated crafting"
	quest.55936801081928A8.quest_desc: [
		"&aPros:&r"
		"&8●&r Taking damage converts it into Wrath"
		"&8●&r Wrath powers repeated Wicked Arcana blasts on hit"
		""
		"&4Cons:&r"
		"&8●&r Incoming damage is doubled"
		"&8●&r Wrath decays over time"
		""
		""
		"&8Pedestal Items:&r"
		"16x Living Flesh"
		"16x Grim Talc"
		"16x Rotten Flesh"
		""
		"&8Central Item:&r"
		"8x Imitation Heart"
		""
		"&8Spirits:&r"
		"32x &#792CECWicked&r"
		"32x &#D546FFArcane&r"
		"16x &#FA9A1FInfernal&r"
		"16x &#CB0CF8Eldritch&r"
	]
	quest.55936801081928A8.quest_subtitle: "Your pain, their pain"
	quest.55C9A6DDAD756BFE.quest_subtitle: "Loot 1000 chest"
	quest.55C9A6DDAD756BFE.title: "Stop! Leave me some stuff!"
	quest.55D11A9056859FDD.quest_desc: ["These wheels can only be crafted by a mechanical crafter due to their enormous size. When two crushing wheels are placed next to each other and rotate in opposite directions, they become an important part of automation. Crushing wheels will refine items thrown in at the top into their more basic components. Sometimes you can even get a bit more material out of the refined items. Chutes placed above and below the crushing wheels allow for items to automatically be input and output."]
	quest.55D11A9056859FDD.title: "Crushing Wheel"
	quest.56045B3E6D5A6A04.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/dogishi_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.5605EBE2FAD407B0.title: "Badlands"
	quest.5643B1D11C1DAD05.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.5643B1D11C1DAD05.title: "Light Temple"
	quest.564D225B5F8DB57B.quest_desc: [
		"It is unknown how the &aVoid Blossom&r came to be. Perhaps a science experiment gone wrong, toxic gas mixing with spore blossoms, or a dark warlock casting a spell. A sentient plant creature living deep within a dungeon. Although not as frightening as other hostiles found inside, it won’t be long before its vines and poisons bring death your way. Along with its &aregenerative abilites&r, this boss can certainly make victory tought. "
		""
		"&7Maybe there is a way to stop regeneration..."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The &aVoid Blossom&r spawns within the &4&kAncient Mines&r."
		""
		"&7HINT: The key to stopping regeneration can made with the mechanical crafter. It is the only recipe that is 6 items wide."
	]
	quest.567AA17FEE8A83DE.quest_desc: [
		"&#6EC1FFSimple Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it empowers nearby hostile creatures."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
	]
	quest.567AA17FEE8A83DE.quest_subtitle: "Strengthen hostile souls"
	quest.5695BF87B3EA0EDB.title: "Prismachasm"
	quest.56C08D961ED46AA3.title: "Chess Board Knight"
	quest.56C4F2C546A23F2C.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/snovy_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.5700D385606A5501.quest_desc: [
		"Many eons ago, an &5enderman&r fell off of the &5End Islands.&r By itself, this is not an uncommon occurrence. But this time, instead of dying to the void, the enderman persevered and survived the experience. It found itself changed, however, and was no longer a mere enderman. Instead, it became something…&dother. &rIt was now able to cause other entities to teleport short distances uncontrollably, giving the &dEndersent&r the upperhand in battle. "
		""
		"With new abilities and a new look also came a new ambition for power. It haunted &5the End,&r turning other endermen into &dEndersent&r like itself and increasing its army. Centuries past and the&d Endersent&r gained a small foothold in &5the End,&r far away from the reaches of the Dragon. Its power and control slipping further into ruin as more mobs and monsters reside in the End."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Endersent is found in the Ruined Tower Remains within &5the End.&r Use an &6Eye of Chorus&r to locate it."
	]
	quest.571CE7B87B36F000.quest_desc: ["Complete white &7Sempiternal Sanctum&r challenge."]
	quest.579E50D9449872AD.quest_desc: [
		"Welcome to Modded Together.  "
		""
		"This first quest line gives a short overview of what waits ahead."
		""
		"Completing quests in this section unlocks new Chatpers in the Questbook."
	]
	quest.579E50D9449872AD.quest_subtitle: "The first step into the story..."
	quest.579E50D9449872AD.title: "&lNew Beginnings&r"
	quest.579E86961E6B04DC.quest_desc: [
		"&bExplorer Maps&r are a core part of the &5Integrated Minecraft&r experience, acting as an expansion of the mapping functionalities provided by the base game. There are maps that can take you to specific biomes or structures. "
		""
		"Look in the &eShopping&r tab on the left menu to see the &bExplorer Maps&r available for you to buy. Some maps cannot be bought and must be obtained through quests."
		""
		"Many of you already know how to use a Map, but here's a quick reference for anyone who's forgotten."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"- The top of the map is &6North&r, and travelling in the &6negative Z direction&r takes you North. The red pole of the &bMagnetic Compass&r also points North, so if it is pointing upwards, you are travelling North."
		""
		"- Left of the map is &6West&r, and travelling in the &6negative X direction&r takes you West. The &bMagentic compass&r will be pointing right."
		""
		"- Right of the map is &6East&r, and travelling in the &6positive X direction&r takes you East. The &bMagentic compass&r will be pointing left."
		""
		"- The bottom of the map is &6South&r, and travelling in the &6positive Z direction&r takes you South. The &bMagentic compass&r will be pointing down."
		""
		"F3 will show the direction you are headed if you ever get confused."
	]
	quest.579E86961E6B04DC.quest_subtitle: "Quick refresher on how Explorer Maps work!"
	quest.57B58710DF031F3E.quest_subtitle: "Feel free choose the one you like, all rainbow"
	quest.57B58710DF031F3E.title: "Rainbow ~"
	quest.57D57FDF4AE53C64.quest_subtitle: "Collect all the eggs!"
	quest.57D57FDF4AE53C64.title: "Life finds a way!"
	quest.57E22AC608667A48.quest_desc: [
		"&aPros:&r"
		"&8●&r Soul Shatter yields increased Arcana"
		"&8●&r Chained Soul Shatters yield even more Arcana"
		""
		"&4Cons:&r"
		"&8●&r Failing to reap spirits builds withdrawal"
		"&8●&r Withdrawal drains hunger over time"
		""
		""
		"&8Pedestal Items:&r"
		"8x Hex Ash"
		"4x Warp Flux"
		""
		"&8Central Item:&r"
