	quest.58AB7435DE810CF2.quest_subtitle: "Measure twice, cut once"
	quest.58CC87ADBE0B75C8.title: "Laurel Forest"
	quest.591049F5DAAE6A75.quest_subtitle: "Increases speed on sand"
	quest.5930BFB02D8F2217.title: "Ancient Mines"
	quest.593386BCED66E75E.quest_desc: [
		"An expedition once built a sturdy iron-clad bunker in Starlight, summoning many golems to defend it. After battles, some golems were left behind, forgotten. Over time, these abandoned guardians became the &9Starlight Golem&r."
		""
		"Though it cannot move without commands, its iron body has oxidized and fused with impurities, becoming &7indestructible&r when it draws energy from Starlight. Over the years, it has strangely gained wisdom, learning to craft technology no one has seen before. Cut off its connection to the dimension, and its metallic shell may soften—if only for a moment."
	]
	quest.593F0A2DD7B6F9B1.quest_subtitle: "Deal 50.000 Damage"
	quest.593F0A2DD7B6F9B1.title: "Brutal Sword"
	quest.5944DCA9D92A2B3C.quest_desc: [
		"&#6EC1FFSimple Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it slowly restores lost stamina of nearby players."
		"Hunger is preserved for longer periods."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
	]
	quest.5944DCA9D92A2B3C.quest_subtitle: "Preserve hunger"
	quest.59477ECC53C6E254.title: "Soul Sand Valley"
	quest.5955FE21E00ED5A7.quest_desc: ["Strong support build, easy to play and also quick regeneration for exploring, helpful in team and simple combat. This build is mixture between Mage build and Gem so it very expensive in cost, do with careful. Take in this build when you have teammate or friends. It is not recommend to do this build in solo as it setting high difficult in gameplay"]
	quest.595647B7C73FBAED.quest_desc: [
		"&bRune Of Sky Tether&r increases jump height."
		""
		"Reduces gravity slightly."
		""
		"Slight fall damage reduction."
	]
	quest.595647B7C73FBAED.quest_subtitle: "Higher jumps"
	quest.59870DC2804ADD01.quest_desc: [
		"Each &6Dragonsteel&r armor set can be upgraded to 3 different sets of armor. "
		""
		"&o&5These 9 armor sets make up the best armor in the game.&r&r"
	]
	quest.598DD8D6CA90A5C2.quest_desc: [
		"&6Sophisticated Backpacks&r add portable storage that can be upgraded and customized."
		""
		""
		"Once equipped, press &6B&r to open it."
		""
		"You can wear backpack on &6Back&r slot."
	]
	quest.598DD8D6CA90A5C2.quest_subtitle: "Portable storage"
	quest.598DD8D6CA90A5C2.title: "Sophisticated Backpacks"
	quest.59B33E1B0B1D2080.quest_desc: [
		"When the&b Dread Queen &rfirst crossed over from the&b Dreadlands&r into the &2Overworld,&r she took the world by (snow)storm. Memorials for those who lost their lives to the &bQueen &rand her army were constructed all throughout the snowy lands she laid claim to. But her powers were greater than previously thought, and her dark magic seeped into these resting sites. Trapped in a crypt under the snow and corrupted by dark magic, the &3Frostbitten Golem &rawaits any unsuspecting adventurer who falls into its cage."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Frostbitten Golem is found in the &3Frozen Crypt. "
	]
	quest.59B9A57BDB1BAFFB.quest_desc: ["&5Ritual brazier&r are used to summon the &4Wilden Chimera&r boss but also can activated with ritual tablets to for various powerful effects. "]
	quest.59CB1704B0CADD3F.quest_subtitle: "Reach lv100"
	quest.59CB1704B0CADD3F.title: "I've done many things"
	quest.59D1C805DC42672E.quest_desc: [
		"The &bCaustic Catalyst&r combines &#FA9A1FInfernal&r and &#1D64E8Aqueous&r forces."
		""
		"It increases Tuning Potency as system instability rises."
		""
		"The more unstable the Crucible, the stronger the effect."
		""
		"High power comes with higher risk."
	]
	quest.59D1C805DC42672E.quest_subtitle: "Power from instability"
	quest.59EDF9AB9BA89BB9.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.59EDF9AB9BA89BB9.quest_subtitle: "Craft the &5Novice Spell Book"
	quest.59EDF9AB9BA89BB9.title: "Into a Magical World"
	quest.59F1AB1383244909.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.59F1AB1383244909.title: "Frozen Crypt"
	quest.59F7DBF03F4A6EE5.quest_subtitle: "{components:{\"ftbquests:loot_crate\":\"relics_ars\"},count:1,id:\"ftbquests:lootcrate\"}"
	quest.5A3900FD2A6F064E.quest_desc: ["Little Tremmy never did anything to you. And this is how you repay him?!?"]
	quest.5A3900FD2A6F064E.quest_subtitle: "You monster. How could you do this?"
	quest.5A51B19A671B71AC.quest_desc: ["Enter a &eCell Maze&r Structure"]
	quest.5A7BBAB95B66F161.quest_desc: [
		"Long ago, the &eEarthrend Monks&r led the world in the study of earth magic. They used their powerful &2geomancy&r to shape mountains and cliffs into monasteries - bastions of education in prayer and self-defense. But those days have passed. The monasteries stand today abandoned and dilapidated. Elemental monsters called &eBluffs&r flood the halls, drawn to the magic left behind."
		""
		"Only one monk remains: &eTongbi, the Sculptor&r. A master of &2geomancy, &eTongbi&r waits in the monastery’s courtyard, challenging visitors to a &6parkour test. &rNever before has a disciple reached the top of this arduous climb, but the one who does will be worthy of the power of the Earthrend Monks.&r The Sculptor will grant them a powerful artifact called the &2Earthrend Gauntlet&r, which gives its wielder control over earth magic."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Use the &6Eye of the Sculptor&r to locate the monastery &eTongbi&r resides in."
		""
		"&bNOTE: This quest is quite different to others. You must beat the parkour challenge, instead of fighting the boss in order to win."
	]
	quest.5A9F07499023CC33.title: "Cursium Armor"
	quest.5AB9F625410298AE.title: "Forests and Groves"
	quest.5ABDA2B5174C1423.quest_desc: ["Basic set early game for spell casting"]
	quest.5ABDA2B5174C1423.title: "Novice"
	quest.5AF35BBC9EE8D023.quest_desc: ["&5Focus of summoning&r can be upgraded to amplify a specific element. "]
	quest.5AF35BBC9EE8D023.title: "Focusing on the elements"
	quest.5B09D9B25751DECC.quest_desc: [
		"&bRune Of Dexterity&r increases movement speed."
		""
		"The lower your health, the stronger the bonus."
		""
		"Can nearly double speed at critical health."
	]
	quest.5B09D9B25751DECC.quest_subtitle: "Faster when near death"
	quest.5B39E2881863EA17.title: "Apothecary Abode"
	quest.5B7069D1204A20D8.quest_desc: [
		"A powerful familiar infused with ender magic and focused on melee combat."
		""
		"&9Abilities:&r"
		""
		"• Can collect Dragon Breath into glass bottles."
		""
		"• Naturally regenerates health."
		""
		"• Will protect nearby allied familiars by intercepting melee attackers."
		""
		"&dHabitat:&r"
		""
		"Found within the &5Outer End Islands&r."
	]
	quest.5B7069D1204A20D8.quest_subtitle: "Ender Knight"
	quest.5B7069D1204A20D8.title: "Dragoon"
	quest.5B8C46802B9ED71F.quest_subtitle: "Take 20.000 Damage"
	quest.5B8C46802B9ED71F.title: "I am a shield"
	quest.5BB2644309CFB988.quest_desc: [
		"A stronger version of the once great &4Dead King&r, he can be summoned to fight once more. This time he will be more difficult to beat, but the rewards will also grow. The key to summoning him is hidden within his &cCatacombs&r."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The &4Enraged Dead King&r is summoned using a &6&kspell&r found within his &cCatacombs&r."
	]
	quest.5BE328A106F065B9.title: "Griefer Armor"
	quest.5BFC87BF25DA2758.quest_subtitle: "{components:{\"ftbquests:loot_crate\":\"refined\"},count:1,id:\"ftbquests:lootcrate\"}"
	quest.5C12F4CC1F6F6C32.quest_desc: ["Looming among the clouds, this massive airship bristles with defenses and hostile crew. Phantom-mounted fiends circle overhead, while fish-like raiders astride hoglins stalk the decks. Boarding it is no small feat. Tthose who triumph will etch their name among the few who dared challenge the skies."]
	quest.5C12F4CC1F6F6C32.quest_subtitle: "Find a Heavenly Challenger"
	quest.5C4362FBF4BB8846.quest_subtitle: "32 Emeralds per Map"
	quest.5C71BF671699BF37.quest_desc: [
		"The ghost of a once great illager captain, &3Captain Cornelia&r was lost, never to be seen again in the &bIce Maze&r. She wanted her crew to be the first to explore this icy domain and return to tell the tale. But alas, she never returned. Rumor has it that with a special conch found on board her fleet of ships has the power to summon her ghost. Her ghost is vengeful, however, and unleashes many deadly abilities on those who summon her. In addition to &3Captain Cornelia's&r offensive capabilities, her regeneration serves as a great defense."
		""
		"&7Maybe there is a way to stop regeneration..."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Use the &6Shell Horn&r to summon &3Captain Cornelia&r. The horn can be found within &k&6the Ship&r in the &bIce Maze&r. You must be in the &bIce Maze&r and &3Deep Frozen Ocean&r for the &6Shell Horn&r to work."
		""
		"&7HINT: The key to stopping regeneration can made with the mechanical crafter. It is the only recipe that is 6 items wide."
	]
	quest.5C777F6B60F7D379.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/taru_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.5C8B9E125EA4FF5B.title: "Brick House"
	quest.5C918104E9B5A332.quest_desc: [
		"Most &6Create&r machines use &eAndesite Alloy&r."
		"Early on, it can be crafted by hand from andesite and iron nuggets."
		"Later, a &eMixer&r can make more with less effort."
		"Making a good supply helps everything else run smoother."
	]
	quest.5C918104E9B5A332.quest_subtitle: "Basic metal for machines"
	quest.5C918104E9B5A332.title: "&lAndesite Alloy&r"
	quest.5C9996876CAE4EED.quest_desc: [
		"The &bMending Diffuser&r uses Living Flesh to trigger restorative effects."
		""
		"After each completed focusing cycle, it has a chance to repair the Impetus slightly."
		""
		"It cannot repair a fractured Impetus."
	]
	quest.5C9996876CAE4EED.quest_subtitle: "Repair the Impetus"
	quest.5C9C1D99976DA6C8.quest_desc: ["Who say mage can't go combat? wear this!"]
	quest.5C9C1D99976DA6C8.title: "Curse Mage"
	quest.5CA186F2C9AD57AE.quest_desc: [
		"&bBrilliance&r is a form of experience tied to the soul."
		""
		"It is used for enchanting and certain repairs."
		""
		"Brilliance can condense into a physical item."
		""
		"It is commonly obtained from special ore deposits left behind by faded souls."
	]
	quest.5CA186F2C9AD57AE.quest_subtitle: "Condensed experience"
	quest.5CD975573ECE25F5.quest_desc: [
		"The &bSoulstained Scythe&r is a stronger version of the scythe."
		""
		"It deals more damage in combat."
		""
		"It still shatters souls and collects &bSpirit Crystals&r."
		""
		"Built for advanced spirit reaping."
	]
	quest.5CD975573ECE25F5.quest_subtitle: "Enhanced spirit weapon"
	quest.5CD975573ECE25F5.title: "Soulstained Scythe"
	quest.5CDDF3402116BADB.quest_desc: [
		"&bSoulstained Armor&r grants &bSoul Ward&r."
		""
		"Soul Ward absorbs most magic damage."
		""
		"It also reduces physical damage."
		""
		"If Soul Ward breaks, it slowly regenerates."
	]
	quest.5CDDF3402116BADB.quest_subtitle: "Defense beyond the physical"
	quest.5CDDF3402116BADB.title: "Soulstained Armor"
	quest.5D245128F6649E1C.quest_desc: ["The &cMissionary&r is a powerful spirit sent to bring chaos to the Overworld. They were created for only one purpose: destroy the Overworld. With the power to control the weather and undead mobs, the &cMissionary&r will stop at nothing to achieve its goal. "]
	quest.5D53829701892FC7.quest_desc: ["You find a &bTattered Note&r in an Abandoned Mineshaft commanding the readers to return to the a civilization's citadel. There are hastily scribbled coordinates on the back."]
	quest.5D53829701892FC7.quest_subtitle: "You find a note summoning the ancient miners to a citadel..."
	quest.5D53829701892FC7.title: "Ancient Mine"
	quest.5D622FEF57894F1F.title: "Escort to the Castle"
	quest.5D966296C42F7294.quest_desc: [
		"&bRune Of Fiery Embrace&r activates when you are on fire."
		""
		"Extinguishes you and grants brief healing."
	]
	quest.5D966296C42F7294.quest_subtitle: "Turn fire into healing"
	quest.5D9C9052D7853368.title: "Magma Land"
	quest.5DBB28D2E8B47D47.quest_desc: [
		"A fiery familiar infused with infernal magic."
		"It burns enemies that dare to approach."
		""
		"&9Abilities:&r"
		""
		"• Attackers are set on fire when they strike the Scorcher."
		""
		"• Grants fire immunity to both itself and its owner."
		""
		"&dHabitat:&r"
		""
		"Often found wandering the hotter regions of the &4Nether.&r"
	]
	quest.5DBB28D2E8B47D47.quest_subtitle: "Flame Warden"
	quest.5DBB28D2E8B47D47.title: "Scorcher"
	quest.5DCF8060165FBBAF.quest_desc: [
		"Until now, spirit magic was used for personal enhancement and crafting."
		"With Totems, spirit arcana can now influence the world itself."
		""
		"Engrave spirits into &6Runewood Logs&r to create runes."
		"Stack these runes above a &#6Runewood Totem Base&r to form a totem pole and perform a Spirit Rite."
		""
		"Each rite follows a pattern and creates a &#D546FFRite Locus&r —"
		"a spark of directed arcane energy that manifests the ritual’s effect."
	]
	quest.5DCF8060165FBBAF.quest_subtitle: "Affect the world with spirit arcana"
	quest.5DCF8060165FBBAF.title: "Totem Magic"
	quest.5DE37518E34ACB1A.quest_subtitle: "Uncover every fossil"
	quest.5DE37518E34ACB1A.title: "Master Archeologist"
	quest.5DE9C42F9E76A839.quest_desc: ["Obtain the Chronicle of Shadows from the mod &eApotheosis&r. Contains details on enchanting changes, potion changes, and villager changes."]
	quest.5DE9C42F9E76A839.quest_subtitle: "More details on Enchanting changes from Apotheosis!"
	quest.5E5191E2220CB59C.title: "Haunted Manor"
	quest.5E9EFD10D91BE754.quest_desc: [
		"Like the copper set, it grants Water Breathing when the &6Backtank&r contains Air Pressure."
		""
		"&eNetherite Helmet&r"
		"Provides fire and lava immunity and improves lava vision."
		""
		"Full fire and lava immunity requires wearing the complete Netherite set and a pressurized &6Backtank&r."
		""
		"&eNetherite Boots&r"
		"Allow ascending in lava by holding the jump key."
	]
	quest.5E9EFD10D91BE754.quest_subtitle: "Advanced diving equipment"
	quest.5EBFABC2F63E7C94.title: "Power transfer"
	quest.5F2255E0F656FE1C.title: "Archeology Jungle Temple"
	quest.5F2C79A0B08FF2E8.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/dosmo_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.5F3168963EE4F8E4.quest_desc: ["You find a &bTattered Note&r in an End City detailing the Fractured Athenaeum. There are hastily scribbled coordinates on the back."]
	quest.5F3168963EE4F8E4.quest_subtitle: "You find a note in an End City"
	quest.5F3168963EE4F8E4.title: "Fractured Athenaeum"
	quest.5F32CEDA146C5AE9.title: "Woodland Mansion"
	quest.5F3B80A9E670FCEA.quest_desc: [
		"In times of old, Giants ruled the &4Nether&r. But now they are gone and only pieces remain. One such piece is the sentient gauntlet of the Giant King. Left behind in the remains of the King’s treasure room, the netherite glove became embedded into the stone in the center of the room. To awaken the gauntlet, mine a piece of the stone. Though the &4Nether Gauntlet&r may look a bit silly, don’t let it “hand” you a defeat. It will use powerful explosions and fire to take you down."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The &4Nether Gauntlet&r is found in the &4Gauntlet Arena&r. Break one of the blocks with eyes on it to spawn the &4Gauntlet&r."
	]
	quest.5F509CFFAF21EEEB.title: "Ancient Archwood Tree"
	quest.5F6C693550555151.title: "Arcane Library"
	quest.5FC95FCD72608AE2.quest_subtitle: "Lookin' good!"
	quest.5FD57F4AFD00EB89.title: "Witches' Treestump"
	quest.6022A98A371D1F22.quest_desc: [
		"As you vanquish the Witch standing before you, you notice a note fall out of their pocket. "
		""
		"It reads &b\"Return to the &5Illusionary Apothecary&r. &bOur research has put us one step closer to finding eternal life. Aid us in our research and we will reward you. Glory to the Adjudicator.\"&r"
		""
		"If you were able to &etalk, or perhaps even &6Haggle&e with a Witch&r, perhaps you'd be able to find this &5Illusionary Apothecary&r. &eThough, you'd have to gain their trust first.&r"
		""
		"&d&oHint on next page:&r&r"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Perhaps if you had a &6Witch's Hat&r, they might be more receptive..."
	]
	quest.6022A98A371D1F22.quest_subtitle: "You find a note describing an Apothecary..."
	quest.6022A98A371D1F22.title: "Rumor: Calling all Apothecaries"
	quest.602899D1C100DCE3.quest_desc: ["&bRune Of Indomitability&r negates incoming knockback."]
	quest.602899D1C100DCE3.quest_subtitle: "No knockback"
	quest.6038D2D0A54E29DF.title: "Aquatic"
	quest.6045821950FFB096.title: "Fisherman's Lodge"
	quest.60560968324CDF2D.title: "Castle"
	quest.607D35CC05763FE4.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5A step to &eimmortality?&r"
	quest.60A9F2B130BE02D5.quest_desc: [
		"Is the End another world—or a dream that never ends? None can say. What’s certain is that both you and the &5Ender Dragon&r exist within it."
		"Legends tell of this creature as the ruler of The End, enforcing its own silent order. Those who enter its realm seldom return, their bodies and minds lost to the &0Void&r."
		""
		"Over ages, the lost have become &8Endermen&r—hollow echoes of who they once were. Perhaps by defeating the dragon, the balance can be restored, and their spirits freed."
	]
	quest.611E0A75AEB395BB.title: "Cherry Grove"
	quest.614FBA80C927D14C.quest_desc: [
		"For those who seek to explore and loot the &dPink Salt Shrine&r deep underground, be warned for it is protected against trespassers. The &dBerserker&r is the guardian of this shrine. What once was a normal zombie became fused with the pink salt within the shrine and turned into the behemoth it now is. It's rage and chaos unparalleled by any others within the cave."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The &dBerserker&r is in the &dPink Salt Shrine&r. This shrine spawns in pink salt caves, typically under mountainous biomes."
	]
	quest.615884269AB07E86.quest_desc: [
		"Although not always hostile, &9hullbreakers&r are foreboding giants that lurk in the depths of the &9Abyssal Chasm&r. They are frightful predators that can reach a size of 14 blocks long. They do not attack on sight, but rather on light. &9Hullbreakers&r have an aversion to anything emitting light and will seek to destroy it at all cost. This could range from a gentle glow squid to the bright floodlights of a submarine. They tend to circle their prey before attacking, so shut your lights off quickly if you notice one of these creatures. "
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&9Hullbreakers&r are found within the &3&kRuins of the Deep&r structure and the &9Abyssal Chasm&r biome."
	]
	quest.617424E9CF47BACC.quest_subtitle: "Collect Jewlery"
	quest.617424E9CF47BACC.title: "Blinged Out!"
	quest.61752469D4924F85.quest_desc: ["After completing many &bBounties&r through the &bBounty Board&r, you've find a &5Note&r containing the location of the legendary &5Redhorn Guild&r. Find it to register with the &5Guild&r and get extra rewards for your hard work."]
	quest.61752469D4924F85.quest_subtitle: "You find a note buried among the bounties..."
	quest.61752469D4924F85.title: "Guildmasters Summons"
	quest.61D996304009E9CE.quest_subtitle: "Increases swim speed"
	quest.61DEAD93BA4A2C67.quest_desc: [
		"&#6EC1FFSimple Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it slowly mends nearby beings."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
	]
	quest.61DEAD93BA4A2C67.quest_subtitle: "Restore vitality"
	quest.6201488BC9F7D831.quest_desc: [
		"&bSoulwoven Banners&r are crafted from Soulwoven Silk."
		""
		"They can be infused with spirits to emit light."
		""
		"Additional spirits increase the intensity of the glow."
		""
		"Used for decoration or marking arcane spaces."
	]
	quest.6201488BC9F7D831.quest_subtitle: "Glowing arcane standard"
	quest.624466592851CD96.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/darknix_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.62495ECB679DED34.quest_desc: ["Max tier glyphs allow to cast in this spell book, every useful glyphs exist in this tier."]
	quest.62495ECB679DED34.title: "Master"
	quest.62C13CF152B69B24.title: "Bamboo Forest"
	quest.62F04F9A5903CF89.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/skinno_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.63116691C92FD576.quest_desc: ["A quiet spring hidden among the hills, its waters swirl mysteriously in the bottomless well. Travelers speak of subtle blessings for those brave enough to approach. Some even report a modest burst of speed for journeys ahead. Whether magic or rumor, the well offers a curious advantage to explorers."]
	quest.63116691C92FD576.quest_subtitle: "Find a Wishing Well"
	quest.63303EC4462B785A.quest_desc: [
		"Think shulkers are annoying to fight? What if it was even worse? The &dShulker Mimic&r was once a regular shulker, but when hit by an offshoot of an Ender and an Eldritch spell colliding, it mutated into a beast that heightens all the worst qualities of shulkers. Not only does the &dShulker Mimic&r make you levitate, but it will bend gravity to its will and toss you around as though you weigh less than a carrot on a stick."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Shulker Mimic is found in the Shulker Tower in &5the End.&r Use an &6Eye of Shulker&r to locate it."
	]
	quest.633E91356C64D6ED.quest_desc: [
		"- &bAnvils&r &6no longer have penalties for prior work&r to reduce the need for EXP grinders and encourage a gradual progression of tool improvement, rather than applying all the enchantments at once."
		""
		"- &bAnvils&r can now be repaired by right-clicking with &bIron Ingots&r"
		""
		"- Renaming items only ever needs 1 level of EXP."
		""
		"All of these changes have been done through &e\"Forgery\"&r!"
	]
	quest.63424CB060AD4AB9.quest_desc: [
		"&#6EC1FFSimple Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it blesses nearby creatures with Sky Tether."
		"Jump height increases while gravity is slightly reduced."
		""
