		"16x &#FA9A1FInfernal&r"
	]
	quest.654073EFE6B79BCF.quest_subtitle: "Rage, rage, against the dying of your might"
	quest.654073EFE6B79BCF.title: "Pact Of Defiance"
	quest.655AA05508658D7C.quest_desc: ["You can connect separate storage system to controller using Storage Tool and Storage Link."]
	quest.656A08444C0E1B92.quest_desc: [
		"&cCreate: Metallurgy&r adds the ability to heat up ores so much that they turn into liquids. &6Mix an ore in a foundry basin to melt it.&r To turn molten metals back into ingots, use fluid pipes to put the molten metal into a mold on a casting table. "
		""
		"Some recipe sequences may require molten metals. Treat it the same as you would any recipe sequence using lava or water. &6One ingot melts down into 144mB of liquid&r."
	]
	quest.656A08444C0E1B92.quest_subtitle: "Is it just me or is it hot in here?"
	quest.656A08444C0E1B92.title: "Metallurgy"
	quest.658F7D00A8E5D76D.quest_desc: ["&bRune Of Vitality&r increases healing received by about 20%."]
	quest.658F7D00A8E5D76D.quest_subtitle: "Stronger healing"
	quest.65AAD6AD8E1E517F.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5A dagger forged with the essence of life!"
	quest.65B65FE2A989ADC8.quest_desc: [
		"&5Rawwrh!&r"
		""
		"Dragons have 5 stages. The ones on the surface are stages 2 and 3. The ones underground are stages 4 and 5. The bigger the dragon, the higher the stage and more difficult the fight. They have been placed under Tier 3 in the Boss Codex since that is middle-of-the-road."
		""
		"&7TIP: Dragon Eggs only drop from stage 4 and 5 &efemale&7 dragons."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Lightning Dragons can be found anywhere in the Overworld as long as the altitude (y-level) is high enough."
	]
	quest.65E170B1002FD845.title: "Crystal Canyon"
	quest.6602E2CF2A7A7B9C.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Millstone&r is a simpler alternative to &6Crushing Wheels&r, used to process items."
		""
		"Items must be inserted from above."
		"Processing speed depends on the &6RPM&r of the machine and the recipe being used."
	]
	quest.6602E2CF2A7A7B9C.quest_subtitle: "&oThe First Grinder&o"
	quest.6602E2CF2A7A7B9C.title: "Millstone"
	quest.660CDDBFA2F7CF3B.quest_subtitle: "A platypus? PERRY THE PLATYPUS?!?"
	quest.6622050B24F69142.quest_desc: [
		"&#6EC1FFSimple Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it blesses nearby creatures with Howling Gale."
		"Movement speed and attack speed are increased."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
	]
	quest.6622050B24F69142.quest_subtitle: "Wind-borne speed"
	quest.662FA8555CAB56CC.quest_desc: ["Connect it to vault for quick way to put items inside. WARNING: You'll need packager to get items back! "]
	quest.6646184B9F25B523.quest_desc: [
		"Once you've freed the &6Villagers&r, you stumble upon a note, containing the &5Evokers Orders&r. Its clear this won't stop until the root cause is dealt with. "
		""
		"However, the surviving &6Illagers&r are fleeing fast and if not immediately followed, you'll likely lose them."
		""
		"On the other hand, while the &6Villagers&r shouldn't be too far from where they came from, they are still poorly equipped to deal with the dangers of the journey home. You could escort them... &6But you'll lose the chance to find the &5Illagers fort&6.&r"
	]
	quest.6646184B9F25B523.quest_subtitle: "You stumble upon a camp of Pillagers, guarding caged Villagers..."
	quest.6646184B9F25B523.title: "The Pillager Camp"
	quest.664A29D238D4345C.quest_subtitle: "Endless colors"
	quest.666633506F508DFC.title: "Enderkeep Courtyard"
	quest.667338706C4A306E.quest_desc: [
		"Spellweaving tools can be enhanced with special enchantments."
		""
		"&8●&r &bWeaver’s Haste&r — loci move significantly faster."
		"Incompatible with Weaver’s Propagation."
		""
		"&8●&r &bWeaver’s Propagation&r — spawns additional loci per level."
		"Incompatible with Weaver’s Haste."
	]
	quest.667338706C4A306E.quest_subtitle: "Modify woven loci"
	quest.667C9BBD6222003F.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/shecko_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.66844AFB7801A221.quest_subtitle: "{components:{\"ftbquests:loot_crate\":\"egg\"},count:1,id:\"ftbquests:lootcrate\"}"
	quest.669BB287B586995D.quest_desc: ["Sturdy sheets help craft a variety of late-game devices. Chunk loaders, storage solutions, and even locomotives!"]
	quest.66C6A9EFF154999E.quest_desc: [
		"&4The Harbinger&r resides in an &4Ancient Factory&r full of technology beyond our comprehension. The greatest creation of it all was the &4Harbinger&r itself. Angered by the treatment of itself and other automatons, the &4Harbinger&r rose up and destroyed its creator. But with that newfound freedom came power and greed. Now the &4Harbinger&r hides away in the &4Factory&r, preparing for the day when it will conquer all of the overworld. "
		""
		"The creator left behind a failsafe just in case this happened. Within the &4Ancient Factory&r there are &cEMP devices.&r The &4Harbinger&r must first charge up the EMPs with its Death Laser, but then they can be activated with redstone, such as a lever, to stun the boss and provide its opponent time to heal and recover or safely attack."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"To awaken the &4Harbinger&r, right-click it with a nether star. Use an &6Eye of Mech&r to locate the &4Ancient Factory&r in the &2Overworld&r."
		""
		"&7HINT: The Harbinger can heal itself using flames. Be wary of any fire, lava, or other heat sources nearby. This includes any spells within the Fire school."
	]
	quest.66E2A5D8A1A92AAA.title: "Mangrove Hut"
	quest.66EA7DEE1464004A.quest_desc: ["Using a &ePattern&r, this machine will input the stored resourced into a connected machine."]
	quest.66EBDFD2C7EF8780.quest_desc: [
		"&6\"Grant Me Source.\""
		"&6\"And I Shall\""
		"&6\"Pave Thy Path.\"  &r"
	]
	quest.66EBDFD2C7EF8780.title: "Buying: Wilden Den Explorer Map"
	quest.67030CEFEC1CEF37.quest_desc: ["Driven from their villages, these hardy merchants now wander the wilds, taking shelter beneath simple cyan and brown tents. Though weary from exile, they still offer trade and refuge to travelers brave enough to seek them out. In a world rising with danger, such camps are rare havens of trust."]
	quest.67030CEFEC1CEF37.quest_subtitle: "Find a Merchant Campsite"
	quest.67160FF0D674100F.title: "Train Ruins"
	quest.67343BA35FE59E7A.title: "The most hurt hit is the hit that no one know"
	quest.673BE438B9516764.quest_desc: [
		"&#6EC1FFSimple Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it slowly harms nearby beings."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
	]
	quest.673BE438B9516764.quest_subtitle: "Slow spiritual decay"
	quest.6741EB11E7C2049E.quest_desc: [
		"Combining &#D546FFArcane&r and &#CB0CF8Eldritch&r in an opposition augment is unstable."
		""
		"The reaction causes a violent explosion."
		""
		"The blast generates &bBlight&r."
		""
		"This is a warning, not a strategy."
	]
	quest.6741EB11E7C2049E.quest_subtitle: "Do not combine blindly"
	quest.677A9F1FFA392B64.title: "Hills"
	quest.67C21FEEACD7C102.quest_desc: ["This manuscript contains unknown powerful spells. Hold right-click to learn these forbidden incantations.  "]
	quest.67C21FEEACD7C102.quest_subtitle: "Ancient Knowledge"
	quest.67DEB218F15BDA0B.title: "Forlorn Hollows"
	quest.67EF8F4FAA3520C8.quest_desc: [
		"Sometimes just a regular crafting table doesn't cut it. You need something bigger and more mechanical! Mechanical crafters can be placed next to one another to make recipes larger than a 3x3 grid. Only one rotational force connection is needed as long as each mechanical crafter is connected in a grid. They can also be added to farms in order to automate crafting productions. Perfect for making an iron farm output blocks instead of ingots or nuggets!"
		""
		"The crafting process starts when every crafter has an item or when the crafter recieves a redstone input. Make sure that the arrows on the crafters are pointed ini a way that brings the slotted items together in the desired way. An exit point for the crafted item is also needed."
		""
		"&8&oThe Mechanical Villager&r &8&oIndustries is not liable in any way, shape, or form for any misuse, malpractice, workplace injuries, or random speaking of french that may arise from using this product. Use at your own risk!"
	]
	quest.67EF8F4FAA3520C8.title: "Mechanical Crafters"
	quest.67F5637BB5847EBB.title: "Willow Forest"
	quest.682FE8DE9C19537C.quest_desc: ["To fill a chunk loader, r-click a ghast with it in your hand. A brass chunk loader will load in a 1x1, 3x3, or 5x5 grid. This is configurable by r-clicking the chunk loader."]
	quest.682FE8DE9C19537C.title: "Brass Chunk Loader"
	quest.6858E25E510AE0FA.quest_desc: ["Drifting through the skies like a colossal squid, this otherworldly airship bristles with defenses. Phantom-riding monstrosities circle its hull, while fish-like warriors astride hoglins guard its decks. To face the Conqueror is to battle a skyborne legion. And only the strongest will claim victory."]
	quest.6858E25E510AE0FA.quest_subtitle: "Find a Heavenly Conqueror"
	quest.6872565204521CB3.quest_desc: [
		"The &aOvergrown Colossus&r is a living representation of the temples found deep in the jungle. Who created these temples and why is still debated, but scholars believe that the temple coming to life in the form of the &aOvergrown Colossus &ris what drove the original architects away…or killed them before they had a chance to leave. "
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Overgrown Colossus is found in the&2 Better Jungle Temple. "
	]
	quest.68950B470C3B36AF.quest_desc: [
		"&bMaledictus&r, a human king, was celebrated for his strength and noble heart. When &4Ignis&r entered the world and laid waste to countless lives, he led his army against the impossible foe."
		""
		"To defeat Ignis, he wielded the &5Soul Render&r—a weapon that curses all who see it, turning them into undead and erasing enemy souls. Victory came, but at a terrible cost: Maledictus himself became undead, stripped of memory, and his soldiers followed the same cursed fate."
		""
		"In a fleeting moment of clarity, he asked to be buried beneath the crypt in the frozen wasteland. The sheer number of undead forced his people to abandon the task, leaving his soldiers to guard the tomb forever."
		""
		"Will you dare to see this cursed place? Craft the &9Eye of Curse&r and witness the legacy of the Undying King."
		"{image:kubejs:textures/quests/cataclysm/maledictus_1_.png width:100 height:100 align:center fit:true}"
	]
	quest.689E8FC6E36FEC08.quest_desc: ["Protection is not enough? This is the fix"]
	quest.689E8FC6E36FEC08.title: "Battle Mage"
	quest.68CEA4A7AB7F3EC7.quest_desc: [
		"Lost deep underground, these heavily armored warriors are neither man nor statue. They may guard something, mourn someone, or await a moment long past—but they have forgotten what, whom, or when."
		""
		"All they know is to slay intruders who enter their chambers. Their armor is &7indestructible&r, yet a single weakness lies at their back—perhaps a sword? Only the bravest adventurers dare face the &8Ferrous Wroughtnaut&r."
	]
	quest.68FDFFAE3BE17592.quest_desc: ["...or well...building anything, I guess. This chapter will showcase decorative blocks, building tools, and more!"]
	quest.6903210043926E19.quest_desc: ["Familiars will look out for neraby beds when they need to recover health."]
	quest.6903210043926E19.quest_subtitle: "Let Your familiars sleep"
	quest.69393606D5ED8058.title: "Redstone Abyss"
	quest.694B82A6E6A653FA.title: "Clover Plains"
	quest.6972903259DED12D.quest_desc: [
		"As you deliver the last of the materials, the Witch motion for you to come closer."
		""
		"&b\"Listen. You did great work collecting these for me. I know a group that are enlisting the help of people like us. I'm short on time, so if you prove to me you have the talent needed to join their group, I'll give you their location.\"&r"
		""
		"They step back."
		""
		"&b\"Either way, its been a pleasure doing business with you. Looking forward to our future endeavors.\"&r"
	]
	quest.6972903259DED12D.quest_subtitle: "If only we could gain their trust..."
	quest.6972903259DED12D.title: "Obtain Information about the Illusionary Apothecary"
	quest.698A347B351C9C0E.quest_desc: ["Craft 6 &ebee nest&r or &ebee hive&r"]
	quest.6994C60E270CEC43.quest_desc: ["&eCreate&r allows for some amazing mechanics using trains. Far more than I could fit in this quest. Make sure to ponder about trains and their components to learn about them in much more detail."]
	quest.69955032DAB8E0C0.quest_desc: [
		"What once must have been a grand pyramid with a bustling village at its base is now abandoned and left for ruin. The reason? A sand creature, the &eDune Sentinel,&r originally summoned to protect the villagers became disillusioned by them after it realized that the villagers took it for granted. Angry by its mistreatment, the &eDune Sentinel&r terrorized the villagers until they moved out. It still remains guarding the &edesert pyramid &rtoday, but no longer does it protect villagers or players."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Dune Sentinel is found guarding the Desert Temple. Use an &6Eye of Sandstorm &rto locate it."
	]
	quest.69CB107DAC0D91F4.quest_subtitle: "burning two side!"
	quest.69D290333BD596B0.quest_subtitle: "You survived 100 days of Integrated Minecraft!! Now you can post your 100 days video"
	quest.69EEBB675F42BB49.quest_desc: [
		"Spirit Rites have a limited area of effect, but it can be hard to see."
		""
		"A special staff can resonate with spirit arcana."
		"While holding it, the range of nearby totems becomes visible."
		""
		"The staff can also tune runes by interacting with them."
		"This activates their visual state even when they are not part of a totem."
	]
	quest.69EEBB675F42BB49.quest_subtitle: "Visualize and tune spirit rites"
	quest.69EEBB675F42BB49.title: "Managing Totems"
	quest.6A0237FADC519965.quest_desc: ["From a distance, it looks peaceful. Fields of golden wheat swaying beside a proud windmill. But don’t be deceived: the Illagers tend no crops for trade. Behind the rustic facade lies a nest of evil, their blades as sharp as the sickles they carry."]
	quest.6A0237FADC519965.quest_subtitle: "Find an Illager Windmill"
	quest.6A13CBC52E320013.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/hyena_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.6A1FA3085162F2D2.quest_desc: [
		"&#1E5AA8Advanced Rite&r"
		""
		"While active, it weaves a Bound Rite Locus."
		"Blocks touched by the Locus rise upward, up to sixteen blocks high."
		""
		"[  ]"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#72EE19✧&r] &#72EE19Earthen&r"
		"[&#D546FF✧&r] &#D546FFArcane&r"
		"[&#CB0CF8✧&r] &#CB0CF8Eldritch&r"
	]
