		"16x &#792CECWicked&r"
	]
	quest.6BD17F61D64105FF.quest_subtitle: "To ignite and watch"
	quest.6BD65F35DF3DA446.quest_desc: [
		"Place the mechanical crafters in a grid like so:"
		""
		"  []"
		"  []"
		"[][][]"
		"[][][]"
		"  []"
		""
		"Input the crafting materials according to the EMI recipe. Be sure that the mechanical crafters are aligned so that the items will move correctly and have a point of exit. Use your new Extendo Grip in your offhand to have extra reach whenever you may need it. This might come in handy for mining, fighting, building, and more!"
		""
		"&l&bVoila!&r You have made a &l&eCreate Creation!&r"
	]
	quest.6BD65F35DF3DA446.quest_subtitle: "Extendo Grip"
	quest.6BD65F35DF3DA446.title: "Practice Time"
	quest.6BE3259975DA9849.title: "Bazaar"
	quest.6BED9713846D601C.quest_subtitle: "Obtain Every Armor Trim"
	quest.6BED9713846D601C.title: "Trimmed Out!"
	quest.6BF3212B4CDCCBAA.quest_desc: [
		"To use tablets, your items must be &9soul-haunted&r."
		""
		"Place a &bsimple grave&r and wait for a soul to appear. Then right-click the grave while holding the item you want to haunt."
	]
	quest.6BF3212B4CDCCBAA.quest_subtitle: "How do I get them?"
	quest.6BF3212B4CDCCBAA.title: "I need souls"
	quest.6BF97B53FE3D64DD.quest_desc: ["Electrum armor makes you &bfaster&r. The faster you are, the &bmore damage&r electrum weapons can deal."]
	quest.6BF97B53FE3D64DD.quest_subtitle: "A Need for Speed"
	quest.6BF97B53FE3D64DD.title: "Electrum Armor"
	quest.6BFE5D35265080E6.quest_desc: ["A sprawling underground stronghold, the Scorched Mines radiate in four cardinal directions from a central dome. Heat and shadows fill the tunnels, and danger lurks at every turn. Brave adventurers who navigate its branching paths may uncover riches, but only if they survive the hazards within."]
	quest.6BFE5D35265080E6.quest_subtitle: "Find the Scorched Mines"
	quest.6C177FB0691F9931.quest_subtitle: "{components:{\"ftbquests:loot_crate\":\"plushie\"},count:1,id:\"ftbquests:lootcrate\"}"
	quest.6C19DD3BA3097690.title: "Manuscript Shrine"
	quest.6C26AEA4620EF6A5.quest_desc: [
		"Elemental arcana embody natural impulses and traits."
		"They are found in creatures, materials, and environments aligned with their nature."
		""
		"&8●&r &#4BF3DAAerial&r — speed and mobility. Found in swift beings and wind-touched sources."
		""
		"&8●&r &#1D64E8Aqueous&r — adaptation and flow. Found in water and aquatic life."
		""
		"&8●&r &#48EE19Earthen&r — stability and vitality. Found in nature and enduring materials."
		""
		"&8●&r &#FA9A1FInfernal&r — fire and light. Found in flame, heat, and nether creatures."
		""
		"Different infusions require different elemental arcana."
	]
	quest.6C26AEA4620EF6A5.quest_subtitle: "Forces of nature given form"
	quest.6C26AEA4620EF6A5.title: "Elemental Arcana"
	quest.6C44C94E3AA6AE2C.quest_desc: ["Provides natural regeneration regardless to how hungry You are"]
	quest.6C44C94E3AA6AE2C.title: "Comfort"
	quest.6C7D6756410EDB21.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.6C7D6756410EDB21.title: "Pink Salt Shrine"
	quest.6C8346BEF1EE2B44.quest_desc: ["This is the main bay for &eStorage Disks&r used to store items in the setup. "]
	quest.6C8346BEF1EE2B44.quest_subtitle: "Don't remove CD while in use!"
	quest.6C950ED208A6728F.quest_desc: [
		"&5Imbument chamber&r will help you craft &5Elemental essence&r and"
		"some equipment. To do so, place down &5Imbuement chamber&r and 8 &5Arcane pedestal&r surround it to have full access to all recipes."
	]
	quest.6CB5ACBAAED66871.quest_desc: ["Shaped from the stem and cap of a giant fungus, this whimsical dwelling offers a rare touch of charm in a perilous world. Lightly guarded and easy to claim, the mushroom house makes for a delightful refuge, perfect for any adventurer who’s ever dreamed of calling a mushroom home."]
	quest.6CB5ACBAAED66871.quest_subtitle: "Find a Mushroom House"
	quest.6CD5D69ED3A5CDDB.quest_subtitle: "Have every effect (potion or not) applied at the same time."
	quest.6CEF5A3A89B7C499.title: "Swampland Terraces"
	quest.6CF1E5CA1BADAA68.quest_subtitle: "Makes Piglins neutral"
	quest.6CF1E5CA1BADAA68.title: "Ruby Armor"
	quest.6D38610803F34744.quest_desc: [
		"As you collect the last sapling, the world around you goes silent. Then, as if planned, words emerge from all around you. Some are made with the soft rustling of leaves, others are filled with the chatter of nearby critters."
		""
		"         &2\"Thank You.\""
		"            &2\"Now.\""
		"   &2\"Please\""
		"      &2     \"Drive out.\""
		"                   &2\"The Evils Within\""
		"                          &2   \"My Roots.\"&r"
		""
		"&6                   \"Grant Me Source.\""
		"&6        \"And I Shall\""
		"&6              \"Pave Thy Path.\"  &r"
	]
	quest.6D38610803F34744.title: "A Whisper on the Winds II"
	quest.6D43D69EEEBE2D79.quest_desc: ["Trade &bSource Gems&r for &bPathfinder Quills&r to locate different biomes!"]
	quest.6D43D69EEEBE2D79.title: "Finding Overworld Biomes"
	quest.6D4CEE9AE7B782E3.quest_desc: [
		"Many &eCreate&r machines include short visual guides through the &bPonder&r feature."
		"These tutorials show how parts connect and move — perfect for learning fast."
		""
		"&8●&r Hold [&bW&r] on a Create item to see it in action."
		"&8●&r Watch, then rebuild what you saw."
		"&8●&r Generators produce energy called &6Stress Units (SU)&r."
		"Each generator can only supply a limited amount."
		""
		"If machines demand more SU than the system provides, the system will stall."
		""
		"&8●&r Machines spin at a speed called &6Rotational Speed (RPM)&r."
		"Higher RPM makes machines work faster."
	]
	quest.6D4CEE9AE7B782E3.quest_subtitle: "&oGuidance for the Aspiring Engineer&o"
	quest.6D4CEE9AE7B782E3.title: "&6&lCreate Tutorials&r"
	quest.6DFE972FAA694B33.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Chain Conveyor&r is mainly used to move Cardboard Packages."
		""
		"It can also transfer rotational power across open spaces, even if the connection is not perfectly aligned."
		"Horizontal, vertical, and diagonal links are supported."
		""
		"A &6Chain Conveyor&r can be linked to another using a Chain."
		"Connections can reach up to &632 blocks&r."
		"To cancel a link, right-click the conveyor again."
		""
		"&8● &6Package Transport&r"
		"Cardboard Packages can be placed directly on conveyors with right-click or inserted automatically using Package Frogports."
		""
		"Conveyors will sort packages by their Address and send them to Frogports with matching destinations."
	]
	quest.6DFE972FAA694B33.quest_subtitle: "Package transport"
	quest.6E0A613837414380.title: "Pyromancer Tower"
	quest.6E38A545F7DEB338.title: "Mediterranean Village"
	quest.6E5169E27C8C2468.quest_desc: ["Bees and their hives hold far more than one might expect. In the Bumblezone, you can explore the nests, observe the daily life of the bees, and meet their queen. The deeper you go, the more secrets you uncover, including powers and rewards that exist only within this buzzing world. Respect the hive, and it may reward you beyond imagination."]
	quest.6E5169E27C8C2468.quest_subtitle: "The Land of Bees"
	quest.6E5169E27C8C2468.title: "&e&lThe Bumblezone&r"
	quest.6E5C712DA54999CB.quest_desc: [
		"&e\"JEI\"&r (short for Just Enough Items) and &e\"EMI\"&r are the items on the right when you open your inventory. Use them to search items and view their recipes. Here's a couple of tricks!"
		""
		"- Press &d\"R\"&r over an item, or &dleft-click&r on it, to view its recipe. Some items like Rotten Flesh will display the mob they are dropped by. Some items will have a tab with an &a\"I\"&r in a circle. Click it to view more information on the item"
		""
		"- Press &d\"U\"&r over an item, or &dright-click&r on it, to view its uses in various recipes."
		""
		"&bContinue on Next Page ->&r"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"You can also search for specific mods with &a\"@\"&r. For instance, try &a\"@endrem\"&r. If you are enjoying items from a specific mod, try looking it up to see what else it has to offer!"
		""
		"&nExamples: &r"
		"@AlexsMobs"
		"@Spelunkery"
		"@Create"
		""
		"&bContinue on Next Page ->&r"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"You can search for specific tags or groups of items with &a\"#\"&r. Try the following!"
		"  "
		"&nExample:&r"
		"  - #starter_kit"
		"  - #villager_job_site"
		"  - #saplings"
		""
		"&bContinue on Next Page ->&r"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Using JEI/EMI on a mob's Spawn Egg can show you what that mob's drops are. Some mobs have information as well attached to their Spawn Eggs. The extra information is usually for mobs with more complicated mechanics. Additional information and lore for many mobs can be found through the &6Animal Dictionary&r."
		""
		"&nExample:&r"
		"Gorilla"
		"Elephant"
		"Bee"
	]
	quest.6E5C712DA54999CB.quest_subtitle: "Learn to use JEI/EMI to search items!"
	quest.6E5C712DA54999CB.title: "JEI/EMI!"
	quest.6E71843C9A5BD219.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/meloron_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.6E7763B06CCCA2B2.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5A blade only for the once that are lost!"
	quest.6E79F813B1309848.quest_desc: ["Hit 24 entities with &6Pollen Puff&r"]
	quest.6E866E9FEDEE2430.quest_desc: ["Breed 6 &6honey slime&r"]
	quest.6EA12AC88F21D977.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5Be Careful it doesnt take ur soul!"
	quest.6ED321B3ABC9C1ED.quest_desc: ["Allows for both, insert and pipe out items from the storage system."]
	quest.6EE3843598020BD2.quest_subtitle: "Feel like i'm burning and so the enemy"
	quest.6EE71408219E782F.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5Burning blade from Hell it self"
	quest.6EF6EAF5EDB68E68.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Blaze Enchanter&r works like an Enchanting Table but requires &6Liquid Experience&r to operate."
		""
		"Before enchanting, select the level in the machine panel."
		"Vanilla enchanting normally caps at level 30."
		""
		"Placing an item in the panel activates &eTemplate Enchanting Mode&r."
		""
		""
		""
		"&eTemplate Enchanting Mode&r"
		"The item placed in the filter slot determines which enchantments can appear."
		""
		"Only enchantments valid for that item type will be generated and stored in an &6Enchanting Template&r."
		""
		"Different item types can produce different enchantments."
		"Higher levels are not always better, as some enchantments only appear at lower levels."
		""
		""
		"&eSuper Enchanting&r"
		"Using &6Super Enchanting&r allows enchantments to exceed vanilla limits."
		""
		""
		"&eIncreasing enchantment levels&r"
		"Transfer the enchantment into a &6Super Enchantment Template&r."
		""
		"Then combine two identical templates in the &6Blaze Forger&r to create a higher level template."
		""
		"Repeat the process until the maximum level is reached."
	]
	quest.6EF6EAF5EDB68E68.quest_subtitle: "Advanced enchanting"
	quest.6EFDB55F9DD2DE4A.title: "Magic combat"
	quest.6F3A522F48723F9D.quest_desc: [
		"&5Magebloom Seed&r can be crafted in hexerei cauldron using 4 Belladona Flowers and 4 Source Gems. Check recipe with clicking on seed."
		""
		"A &5Source berry&r can also provide source mana via a &5source link&r device. Beyond that, the foods made from these berries will provide a buff to mana regeneration. "
	]
	quest.6F3A522F48723F9D.quest_subtitle: "Farming is the key"
	quest.6F3A522F48723F9D.title: "Farming Again?"
	quest.6F3E0DADC7E5D1B5.quest_desc: [
		"Make sure to check JEI/EMI first before asking for help from one of the devs. Many recipes have been edited or completely changed to better fit the idea of &o&6integration&r. Recipes now require items from various mods instead of just one mod and/or vanilla."
		""
		"Some recipes are hidden on purpose. Check &e\"Why isn't _____ in JEI/EMI?\"&r for more information on this."
		""
		"Make sure you are using the correct recipe for &othis&r modpack and not from a different one. If the problem still persists, reach out on our discord. "
	]
	quest.6F4219D5D01B5958.quest_desc: [
		"Scythes can be enchanted like other weapons."
		"They accept common enchantments such as Unbreaking."
		""
		""
		"They also have unique enchantments:"
		""
		"&8●&r &bHaunted&r increases soul impact damage"
		""
		"&8●&r &bAscension&r improves mobility, incompatible with Rebound"
		""
		"&8●&r &bRebound&r allows the scythe to return when thrown"
		""
		"&8●&r &bSpirit Plunder&r increases spirit yield but strains durability"
		""
		"Choose carefully. Some enchantments conflict."
	]
	quest.6F4219D5D01B5958.quest_subtitle: "Empowering the blade"
	quest.6F4219D5D01B5958.title: "Scythe Enchanting"
	quest.6F575FD4C27C64D8.title: "Gauntlet Arena"
	quest.6F7DAC2D906DFD4B.quest_subtitle: "Kill 1000 Pillager"
	quest.6F7DAC2D906DFD4B.title: "Dare to come again?"
	quest.6F7EE5B63C91A70F.quest_desc: ["Two basic tables from Ars - the Scribe is for spell crafting and Alteration to upgrade armor, equipment and bind spells to equipment."]
	quest.6F7EE5B63C91A70F.title: "Scribe and Alteration"
	quest.6FACE97C88427A54.quest_desc: ["Once a simple underground Venus trap, the &5Void Blossom&r evolved after the Blood Moon, absorbing &8Void&r energy to become faster, deadlier, and able to attack over a wide area with spikes."]
	quest.6FB0DC24A262CBF9.quest_desc: [
		"Opens the grave and gives Your items back."
		"You can right click on haunted grave to teleport to Your death location."
	]
	quest.6FB0DC24A262CBF9.quest_subtitle: "Opens Your grave :)"
	quest.6FFD064208CB6FE5.title: "Phantom Citadel"
	quest.700ECEC8C332E809.title: "Terrible Armor"
	quest.7014F6992A42EFB1.quest_subtitle: "Makes most undead mobs neutral to the player. Increases block reach"
	quest.7018999749A4E9FC.quest_desc: [
		"&cThe Netherite Monstrosity&r was created in a freak accident many years ago. A blacksmith was testing out a new invention involving lava, netherite, and liquid hyper experience when he was attacked by a Ghast and fell into the mixture. When he emerged, it was no longer as a human, but something else, something &cMonstrous&r. He became angry at the world and all those within. He still to this day lives within his forge, the &cSoul Blacksmith&r, practising with his fiery powers and destroying anyone who comes near."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Netherite Monstrosity will awaken as soon as you near it the Soul Blacksmith structure. Use an &6Eye of Monstrous&r to find the Soul Blacksmith while inside the &4Nether&r."
	]
	quest.7020B22574DDAE5E.quest_desc: [
		"&bRune Of Culling&r increases Scythe damage to targets at or below half health."
		""
		"Bonus damage is roughly 40%."
	]
	quest.7020B22574DDAE5E.quest_subtitle: "Stronger against the wounded"
	quest.702108079F637B75.quest_desc: ["You wish the &6Villagers&r well, assured that they'd be able to safely return. You then begin the long and arduous process of track the surviving &6Illagers&r to find where they came from."]
	quest.702108079F637B75.quest_subtitle: "Incompatible with \"Lead to Safety\""
	quest.70327C3AC547B354.quest_desc: ["Marked by its dark prismarine and yellow terracotta roof, this temple has long since fallen to corruption. Inside, swarms of spider-like creatures creep through its halls, striking with venom and ferocity. To enter is to step into a nest where every shadow crawls."]
	quest.70327C3AC547B354.quest_subtitle: "Find an Infested Temple"
	quest.703710C8CC4AD4D9.title: "Ingot store"
	quest.7050720F2F088387.quest_desc: ["Use on haunted grave, You will get long term positive effects. "]
	quest.7050720F2F088387.quest_subtitle: "Gives long term effects"
	quest.7052C9A5A804E866.quest_desc: ["A riot of color rises from the wilderness, marking the territory of a cunning band of raiders. Their homes are bright and inviting, but enter at your own risk. These defenders strike fast and often. Those who prevail will find spoils and secrets hidden among the lively façades."]
	quest.7052C9A5A804E866.quest_subtitle: "Find a Bandit Village"
	quest.70581D79FC865B4C.quest_desc: ["A dark purple toadstool hiding among nether fungi. Ignored by hoglins but eaten by their undead kin. It reeks of rot, though alchemy may draw out its entropic power."]
	quest.70581D79FC865B4C.quest_subtitle: "Fungus of Decay"
	quest.706E41199B308C92.title: "Tropics"
	quest.70776C37B0B7F00F.quest_desc: [
		"Those who fled the Ender Dragon built the &7End Citadel&r, a fortress filled with deadly traps to keep intruders away."
		""
		"Time and the &0Void&r corrupted them, twisting the once-loyal guards into &8Ender Golems&r. Their king, trapped on the lowest floor, became the &5Ender Guardian&r."
		""
		"They no longer remember life, acting only to defend the citadel. Some say they still wait for a hero to release them from this cursed fate. To see the truth, you will need the &dEye of Void&r."
		"{image:kubejs:textures/quests/cataclysm/ender_guardian.png width:100 height:100 align:center fit:true}"
	]
	quest.70965B7B1E10E72E.quest_subtitle: "{components:{\"ftbquests:loot_crate\":\"ars\"},count:1,id:\"ftbquests:lootcrate\"}"
	quest.70B89204B24F897B.quest_desc: [
		"Use this at a &5Ritual brazier&r to summon a &4Wilden Chimera&r boss. You will need to active the tablet first."
		""
		"The &4Wilden Chimera&r is a strong boss with 1000 HP, prepare yourself and your gear before taking on the challenge!"
	]
	quest.70C8BA5815937256.title: "Cullinary Master"
	quest.70D116BC58038638.quest_desc: [
		"&4Ignis&r is one of, if not &othe greatest&r adversary within &6Integrated Minecraft&r. Taking on this foe requires careful preparation and a strong understanding of his mechanics. The &4Ignis&r is a god-like being, perhaps even a god itself. No one has ever returned from setting off to battle this foe, so there is little information to go off of. So utterly threatening is the Ignis, that only it and its bodyguards reside within the &4Burning Arena&r. Wither Skeletons, Piglins, and Ghasts are all too afraid to enter. Are you?"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"To summon Ignis, you will need to first slay his bodyguards, the Ignited Revenants. They will drop Burning Ashes which can be used on the Altar of Fire to summon Ignis. Use the &6Eye of Flame&r to locate the Burning Arena within the &4Nether&r."
	]
	quest.71060AC2A4183A07.title: "Toxic Caves"
	quest.7128682DF064EB5A.title: "Archmage Tower"
	quest.716AD8FF75AE8232.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/taru_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.716D88AB186E4DEF.title: "Beekeeper's House"
	quest.71C8997F920EB5E3.title: "End City"
	quest.71CC32DB4E1F3285.quest_desc: ["This hat bag will &4NOT&r drop in normal day and will only drop in holliday or festival. If you can not wait then here take it with a cheap price. These hat contain &bSpecial Effect&r based on festival type."]
	quest.71CC32DB4E1F3285.title: "Festi ~"
	quest.71EEA285EB464740.quest_desc: [
		"A normal workbench can’t handle magic."
		"With &bRefined Soulstone&r and &6Runewood&r, you can make things it never could."
	]
	quest.71EEA285EB464740.quest_subtitle: "Magic needs the right tools"
	quest.71EEA285EB464740.title: "Starting Magic"
	quest.71F8C12A6FF58BD3.quest_desc: ["Breed and get 8 &ebaby bees&r"]
	quest.72081153F57233FA.quest_subtitle: "{components:{\"ftbquests:loot_crate\":\"malum\"},count:1,id:\"ftbquests:lootcrate\"}"
	quest.721ADE33D5D8478F.quest_desc: ["Tier 2 spell book allow you to cast tier 2 glyphs. Enough for combat at this tier"]
	quest.721ADE33D5D8478F.title: "Expert"
	quest.722CF9AA7E95C28E.title: "Ancient Factory"
	quest.72375066092E95D3.title: "Deserts and Dunes"
	quest.7245C47C3CCC10F6.quest_desc: [
		"A distant relative of the &5Obsidilith&r, the &dEnder Guardian&r resides within the &5End&r. Appearing as part of an End City itself, it is thought that the &dEnder Guardian&r is a physical manifestation of the &dRuined Citadel&r. This creature is extremely solitary and will fight anyone who imposes on its home. To prevent intruders, the &dEnder Guardian&r has fitted the &dRuined Citadel&r with a variety of traps. Be careful where you step."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Approach the Altar on the lowest level of the Ruined Citadel to wake the Ender Guardian. Use an &6Eye of Void&r to locate the Ruined Citadel while in the &5End&r dimension."
	]
	quest.726B63D654B3A4F2.title: "Nether Grasslands"
	quest.728DDA6508DCDA12.quest_subtitle: "Ore is found in the End. Two progression paths"
	quest.728DDA6508DCDA12.title: "Terminite Armor"
	quest.72C028074D0645D2.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5Axe Born from hell it self!"
	quest.72C8FDDBB7EEEDF8.quest_desc: ["When connected to a powered &eController&r, this cable will provide energy to all connected components in a refined storage setup."]
	quest.72FEE510C549DC11.quest_desc: [
		"Right-click and hold to spin the crank counter-clockwise, or hold Shift and right-click to reverse the rotation."
		""
		"The Hand Crank operates at a fixed speed of 32 RPM."
	]
	quest.72FEE510C549DC11.quest_subtitle: "Raw strength"
	quest.731D092CBEF73010.quest_desc: [
		"First, craft an &bAlchemical Impetus&r."
		""
		"Place it on the &bSpirit Crucible&r."
		""
		"Insert at least:"
		"&8●&r 2x &#48EE19Earthen Spirit&r"
		"&8●&r 2x &#FA9A1FInfernal Spirit&r"
		""
		"The process creates arcane nodes."
		""
		"Smelt the nodes to obtain nuggets."
		""
		"The Impetus is damaged during focusing."
	]
	quest.731D092CBEF73010.quest_subtitle: "Channel and transmute arcana"
	quest.731D092CBEF73010.title: "Spirit Focusing"
	quest.7331B766323137A2.title: "War-den"
	quest.734BEA705A36799C.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/careyatros_eng2.png width:151 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.73D5EE5238C37982.quest_desc: ["In the wilds rests the skeletal form of a great creature. its skeleton stretching skyward like branches of pale bone. Whether a relic of forgotten myth or a beast once hunted to extinction, none can say. Its silent frame endures as a monument to creatures long lost."]
	quest.73D5EE5238C37982.quest_subtitle: "Find a Ceryneian Hind"
	quest.73D660B9873BEE68.quest_subtitle: "&l&n&5A axe Forged in the cold!"
	quest.73F191A33FAA8878.quest_desc: ["&bRune Of Scorching&r doubles fire damage you deal."]
	quest.73F191A33FAA8878.quest_subtitle: "Stronger fire damage"
	quest.7424F32388952010.quest_desc: ["{image:gamma_creatures:textures/screens/banndu_eng2.png width:150 height:100 align:center fit:true}"]
	quest.7433CAFEFD3AC55F.quest_subtitle: "Loot 100 chest"
	quest.7433CAFEFD3AC55F.title: "Where my diamond go?"
	quest.744273A33517A998.title: "Boreal Tundra"
	quest.745086C99829C9E5.quest_desc: [
		"- Enchanting has been overhauled through &e\"Apotheosis\"&r. Upgrade your enchanting set up with higher tier bookshelves to get better results!"
		""
		"- The EXP needed for max-level enchanting (through Apotheosis) has been greatly increased. However, now &670% of your EXP is dropped on death and the EXP scaling between levels has been greatly reduced&r."
		""
		"- &6Enchantment books found in chests are now limited in level&r to encourage enchanting through the &bEnchanting Table&r. They can still be upgraded in &bAnvils&r (see Anvil tweaks)."
	]
	quest.745086C99829C9E5.title: "Enchanting and EXP Tweaks"
	quest.74550D01582163E0.quest_desc: ["A &eGrid&r with the ability to create a &ePattern&r."]
	quest.7474E81497ACE677.title: "Bayou"
	quest.748BA2DB0F36CC4C.quest_desc: [
		"Created through a sacrificial ritual performed by Underzealots, &4Forsaken&r are large hostile mobs with sound-based attacks. They fight foes with sonic waves in addition to a variety of melee strikes from their upper arms, and can leap around to gain a better position. Although weaker than a Warden’s sonic blast, it can still pack a punch and pierce through armor. "
		"Fun Fact: &4Forsaken&r are immune to the &3Warden’s&r sonic blast but the &3Warden&r can be damaged extra by the &4Forsaken’s&r sonic attack."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Forsaken are found within the &4Forlorn Hollows&r biome only when &6Underzealots&r sacrifice &6Vespers&r."
	]
	quest.748C315A77D2E486.quest_desc: [
